%3BPolysecure%2C%26quot%3B%20has%20become%20the%20poly%20bible%20for%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnn.com%2F2024%2F01%2F25%2Fus%2Fgen-z-adults-lgbtq-identity-reaj%2Findex.html%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520report%2520found%2520about%252016%2C%252C%25E2%2580%259D%2520according%2520to%2520the%2520report.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eincreasingly%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20queer%20and%20fluid%20generation.%20On%20apps%20like%20Feeld%2C%20it's%20not%20uncommon%20to%20see%20people%20flaunting%20copies%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Ethe%20way%20straight%20men%20on%20Tinder%20pose%20with%20a%20freshly%20caught%20fish.%20Recently%2C%20my%20friend%20and%20I%20were%20discussing%20the%20book%20in%20the%20sauna%20at%20the%20Russian%20Baths%20in%20downtown%20Manhattan%20when%20a%20ponytailed%20man%20with%20%26quot%3Bif%20not%20now%2C%20when%26quot%3B%20tattooed%20on%20his%20chest%20interrupted%20to%20say%20the%20book%20changed%20his%20life.%20%26quot%3BThe%20one%20good%20thing%20my%20therapist%20did%20in%20eight%20years%20was%20recommend%20that%20book%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20leaning%20in%20for%20a%20sweaty%20fist%20bump.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESomehow%2C%20Fern%2C%20now%2044%2C%20matched%20with%20%26quot%3Bthe%20one%20person%26quot%3B%20on%20Feeld%20%26quot%3Bwho%20hadn't%20heard%20of%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20At%20the%20time%2C%20she%20was%20living%20in%20Asheville%20with%20her%20son%2C%20her%20ex-husband%2C%20and%20her%20boyfriend.%20John%2C%20a%20video%20editor%20in%20a%20%26quot%3Bdon't%20ask%2C%20don't%20tell%26quot%3B%20situation%20with%20his%20then-wife%2C%20was%20advertising%20himself%20on%20the%20app%20as%20an%20%26quot%3Bexperienced%20bull%20for%20hot%20wives%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20typically%20involved%20having%20sex%20with%20women%20whose%20husbands%20watched%20in%20real%20time%20or%20on%20tape.%20But%20the%20pair%20had%20a%20deeper%20connection%20from%20the%20get-go.%20%26quot%3BI%20could%20just%20tell%20by%20his%20photo%2C%20I%20was%20like%2C%20that's%20the%20one%2C%26quot%3B%20Fern%20said.%20(John%20liked%20the%20way%20Fern%20communicated%20and%20how%20%26quot%3Bher%20ass%20looked%20in%20her%20yoga%20pants%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20me%20over%20the%20phone.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20past%20few%20years%2C%20consensual%20nonmonogamy%20%E2%80%94%20the%20practice%20of%20having%20multiple%20romantic%20or%20sexual%20partners%20at%20a%20time%20%E2%80%94%20has%20popped%20up%20everywhere%20from%20highbrow%20dramas%20like%20%26quot%3BSuccession%26quot%3B%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Eand%20%26quot%3BThe%20White%20Lotus%26quot%3B%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Eto%20goofy%20reality%20shows%20like%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3E%26quot%3BCouple%20to%20Throuple%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%26quot%3B%20The%20New%20York%20Times%20ran%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2Finteractive%2F2024%2F04%2F15%2Fmagazine%2Fpolycule-polyamory-boston.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ea%20story%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20April%20about%20a%2020-person%20polycule%20(a%20group%20of%20people%20intertwined%20in%20a%20network%20of%20intimate%20relationships).%20Molly%20Roden%20Winter's%20best-selling%20memoir%2C%20%26quot%3BMore%2C%26quot%3B%20about%20her%20life%20as%20a%20Park%20Slope%20mom%20in%20an%20open%20marriage%2C%20faced%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theatlantic.com%2Fideas%2Farchive%2F2024%2F02%2Fpolyamory-ruling-class-fad-monogamy%2F677312%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ebacklash%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20depicting%20polyamory%20as%20yet%20another%20self-improvement%20tool%20for%20rich%20white%20people%2C%20while%20Miranda%20July's%20%26quot%3BAll%20Fours%26quot%3B%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Elaunched%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ean%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2024%2F06%2F08%2Fstyle%2Fmiranda-july-all-fours-group-texts.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Earmada%20of%20group%20chats%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20full%20of%20women%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ewondering%20whether%20it%20might%20be%20time%20to%20spice%20things%20up%20with%20a%20younger%20boy%20toy%2C%20an%20older%20girlfriend%2C%20or%20both.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20consensual%20nonmonogamy%20went%20mainstream%2C%20searches%20for%20Fern's%20%26quot%3BPolysecure%26quot%3B%20spiked.%20The%20book%20has%20become%20a%20sleeper%20hit%20since%20coming%20out%20in%202020%2C%20selling%20more%20than%20300%2C000%20copies.%20%26quot%3BI've%20heard%20authors%20joke%20they%20get%20a%20cup%20of%20coffee%20from%20their%20book%2C%26quot%3B%20Fern%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20got%20more%20than%20a%20few%20cups%20of%20coffee.%26quot%3B%20It%20continues%20to%20sell%20around%20350%20copies%20a%20week%2C%20according%20to%20Nielsen%20BookScan%2C%20and%20is%20frequently%20one%20of%20the%20first%20resources%20recommended%20to%20poly%20newbies.%20One%20recent%20convert%20told%20me%20she%20refers%20to%20the%20book%20like%20%26quot%3Ba%20religious%20text.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConsensual%20nonmonogamy%20posits%20that%20people%20can%20be%20romantically%20and%20sexually%20attracted%20to%20more%20than%20one%20person%20at%20once%2C%20in%20many%20different%20arrangements%2C%20and%20that%20jealousy%20around%20those%20feelings%20can%20be%20overcome.%20To%20explain%20how%20it%20works%2C%20Fern%2C%20a%20therapist%20with%20a%20master's%20degree%20in%20conflict%20analysis%20and%20resolution%2C%20draws%20on%20a%20long-standing%20concept%20in%20psychology%20called%20attachment%20theory%2C%20which%20categorizes%20people's%20relationship%20styles%20as%20either%20secure%2C%20anxious%2C%20avoidant%2C%20or%20disorganized.%20As%20Fern%20notes%2C%20relationships%20thrive%20when%20both%20partners%20are%20securely%20attached.%20Because%20poly%20relationships%20can't%20rely%20as%20much%20on%20the%20rites%20of%20passage%20monogamous%20couples%20use%20to%20feel%20safe%20%E2%80%94%20shared%20bank%20accounts%2C%20white%20dresses%2C%20and%20diamond%20rings%20%E2%80%94%20the%20focus%20instead%20must%20be%20on%20optimizing%20the%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%26quot%3Bquality%20of%20experience%26quot%3B%20among%20partners.%20Once%20you've%20figured%20it%20out%2C%20you%20can%20be%20%26quot%3Bpolysecure%2C%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3Bsecurely%20attached%20to%20multiple%20romantic%20partners%26quot%3B%20at%20once%2C%20Fern%20writes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPart%20of%20the%20book's%20mass%20appeal%20is%20that%20it%20also%20resonates%20with%20monogamous%20people.%20If%20you%20look%20at%20Fern's%20steps%20for%20nurturing%20relationships%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%E2%80%94%3Cspan%3E%20%26quot%3Bprocess%2C%20communicate%2C%20grow%2C%20and%20then%20process%2C%20communicate%20and%20grow%20some%20more%26quot%3B%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%E2%80%94%20%3Cspan%3Ea%20lot%20of%20monogamous%20couples%20are%20on%20autopilot%2C%20if%20not%20asleep%20at%20the%20wheel.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%26quot%3BIt's%20like%2C%20OK%2C%20we're%20married.%20We%20don't%20need%20to%20talk%20about%20anything%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20my%20friend%20Hannah%20said.%20While%20she%20has%20always%20been%20straight%20and%20monogamous%2C%20she%20found%20the%20book%20a%20few%20years%20ago%20after%20an%20ex%20cheated%20on%20her%20and%20she%20was%20looking%20for%20less%20black-and-white%20advice%20around%20jealousy%20than%20her%20friends%20or%20%26quot%3Bboomer%20parents%26quot%3B%20could%20provide.%20%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20the%20skills%26quot%3B%20required%20for%20nonmonogamous%20relationships%20%26quot%3Bare%20actually%20necessary%20for%20monogamy%20to%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Fern's%20ex-husband%20and%20collaborator%2C%20Dave%20Cooley.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221429%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Dave%20Cooley%20and%20Jessica%20Fern%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66d7773214a5cd1fcc8ceb76%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221035%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWhen%20Jessica%20Fern%20and%20Dave%20Cooley%20opened%20up%20their%20relationship%2C%20Cooley%20was%20surprised%20at%20the%20%26quot%3Bsearing%20anguish%26quot%3B%20he%20felt%20about%20his%20wife%20seeing%20other%20men.%20%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20Jessica%20Fern%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20other%20part%20was%20timing.%20%26quot%3BPolysecure%26quot%3B%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Ewas%20published%20right%20as%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Erelationship%20therapists%20like%20Esther%20Perel%2C%20Dan%20Savage%2C%20and%20Orna%20Guralnik%20%E2%80%94%20who%20worked%20with%20a%20polycule%20on%20the%20most%20recent%20season%20of%20her%20Showtime%20series%20%26quot%3BCouples%20Therapy%26quot%3B%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%94%20were%20becoming%20household%20names.%20Attachment%20theory%2C%20in%20particular%2C%20had%20captured%20the%20zeitgeist%3B%20TikToks%20of%20people%20analyzing%20their%20attachment%20styles%20and%20categorizing%20pop-culture%20characters%20(Ross%20Geller%3A%20anxious%3B%20Mr.%20Big%3A%20avoidant)%20have%20racked%20up%20millions%20of%20views.%20Older%20texts%20like%201997's%20%26quot%3BThe%20Ethical%20Slut%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20written%20by%20two%20radical%20kink-positive%20feminists%20who%20envisioned%20a%20%26quot%3Bslut%20utopia%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20were%20easy%20to%20dismiss%20as%20the%20purview%20of%20kooky%20lesbian%20bookstores.%20But%20%26quot%3BPolysecure%26quot%3B%20was%20approachable%2C%20speaking%20in%20the%20gentle%20self-help%20jargon%20that's%20become%20this%20generation's%20lingua%20franca.%20For%20readers%20who%20have%20spent%20years%20in%20therapy%2C%20Fern's%20version%20of%20consensual%20nonmonogamy%20was%20less%20a%20radical%20reimagining%20than%20advanced%20dating%20for%20those%20who'd%20mastered%20Relationships%20101.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecoming%20sexually%20or%20romantically%20involved%20with%20someone%20who%20isn't%20your%20partner%20has%20long%20been%20viewed%20as%20the%20cardinal%20sin%20of%20relationships%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20caused%20the%20dissolution%20of%20families%2C%20businesses%2C%20and%20empires.%20Yet%2C%20%26quot%3Bmost%20of%20us%20are%20not%20innately%20only%20drawn%20to%20one%20human%20forever%2C%26quot%3B%20Fern%20said.%20%26quot%3BPolysecure%26quot%3B%20put%20forward%20a%20simple%20and%20compelling%20idea%3A%20What%20if%20this%20is%20not%20only%20OK%2C%20but%20a%20better%20way%20of%20doing%20business%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20past%20year%2C%20%26quot%3BPolysecure%26quot%3B%20has%20entered%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fknowyourmeme.com%2Fphotos%2F2779330-polysecure-in-the-trash%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ememe%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20era.%20In%20March%2C%20someone%20on%20X%20posted%20a%20photo%20of%20two%20copies%20of%20the%20book%2C%20with%20its%20distinctive%20yellow%20cover%2C%20dumped%20in%20a%20cardboard%20box%20labeled%20%26quot%3Bfree.%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BI%20hope%20they're%20doing%20okay%2C%26quot%3B%20read%20the%20caption.%20The%20post%20got%2034%2C000%20likes.%20%26quot%3BReading%20polysecure%20in%20my%20local%20cat%20cafe%20to%20try%20to%20get%20the%20hot%20butch%20barista%20to%20notice%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20another%20X%20user%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BSPOTTED%3A%20bill%20deblasio%20at%20riis%20beach%20reading%20polysecure%20in%20a%20patrick%20church%20speedo%26quot%3B%20someone%20joked%20when%20the%20former%20mayor%20announced%20he%20was%20planning%20to%20separate%20from%20(but%20still%20cohabitate%20with)%20his%20wife%2C%20Chirlane%20McCray.%20In%20August%2C%20the%20singer%20and%20actor%20Suki%20Waterhouse%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tiktok.com%2F%40suki_waterhouse%2Fvideo%2F7400899753283833120%3Flang%3Den%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eposted%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20video%20of%20herself%2C%20scored%20to%20one%20of%20her%20breakup%20songs%2C%20captioned%2C%20%26quot%3Bme%20when%20I%20see%20Jessica%20Fern%20on%20his%20Amazon%20wishlist.%26quot%3B%20My%20former%20coworker%20Allison%20P.%20Davis%2C%20who%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thecut.com%2Farticle%2Fpolycule-polyamourous-relationship-meaning.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ewrote%20a%20cover%20story%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20polyamory%20for%20New%20York%20Magazine%2C%20said%20she%20and%20a%20friend%20started%20keeping%20a%20tally%20of%20the%20number%20of%20copies%20they%20saw%20abandoned%20around%20Fort%20Greene%20and%20Clinton%20Hill.%20(They%20got%20up%20to%20around%2010%20this%20spring.)%20Davis%20ditched%20hers%20on%20her%20front%20stoop%20after%20her%20last%20poly%20relationship%20blew%20up%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Efrustrated%20by%20how%20the%20book's%20terminology%20was%20being%20%26quot%3Bweaponized%20by%20straight%20heteronormative%20people%20who%20are%20doing%20ethical%20nonmonogamy%20badly.%26quot%3B%20Which%20she%20acknowledged%20isn't%20Fern's%20fault.%20But%2C%20she%20added%2C%20%26quot%3BI'm%20blaming%20the%20book.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20brandishing%20%26quot%3BPolysecure%26quot%3B%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Eas%20a%20symbol%20of%20sexual%20enlightenment%20cheapens%20Fern's%20message%2C%20which%20is%20that%20there%20are%20no%20shortcuts%20to%20a%20functional%20relationship%20%E2%80%94%20singular%20or%20plural.%20Fern%20says%20those%20hoping%20%26quot%3BPolysecure%26quot%3B%20will%20be%20a%20sexy%20romp%20that%20teaches%20them%20how%20to%20have%20it%20all%20are%20likely%20to%20be%20disappointed.%20During%20our%20interview%2C%20the%20author%20makes%20it%20clear%20that%20nonmonogamous%20relationships%20are%20just%20as%20pedantic%20and%20grueling%20as%20conventional%20relationships%2C%20if%20not%20more%20so.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20feel%20like%20my%20mission%20is%20to%20be%20this%20advocate%20for%20polyamory%20or%20deconstruct%20monogamy%20itself%2C%26quot%3B%20Fern%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20more%20just%20to%20say%2C%20you're%20allowed%20to%20do%20either.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EFern%20lives%2030%20minutes%20outside%20Asheville%2C%20down%20a%20winding%20backcountry%20road.%20%26quot%3BThis%20here%20is%20some%20'Hills%20Have%20Eyes'%20shit%2C%26quot%3B%20my%20Uber%20driver%20says%20as%20we%20take%20a%20wrong%20turn%20onto%20a%20dead%20end%20full%20of%20rusted%20trailers.%20Pulling%20up%20to%20Fern's%20four-bedroom%20yellow-clapboard%20house%2C%20the%20vibe%20is%20thankfully%20more%20pastoral-quaint%20than%20cannibal-murdery%2C%20but%20it%20still%20feels%20a%20world%20away%20from%20the%20Park%20Slope%20brownstones%20and%20San%20Francisco%20lofts%20where%20%26quot%3BPolysecure%26quot%3B%20has%20become%20required%20reading.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFern%20is%20waiting%20outside%20to%20greet%20me%20in%20a%20purple%20spandex%20athleisure%20dress%20and%20a%20straw%20sunhat.%20Her%20bangs%2C%20round%20cheeks%2C%20and%20big%20blue%20eyes%2C%20ooze%20%26quot%3BGilmore%20Girls%26quot%3B%20wholesomeness%20%E2%80%94%20but%20the%20gold%20spacers%20glinting%20in%20her%20ears%20and%20the%20steely%20resolve%20in%20her%20voice%20suggest%20otherwise.%20Fern%20gives%20me%20a%20tour%20around%20the%20expansive%20property%2C%20which%20includes%20a%20blue-shingled%20house%20for%20her%20mom%20across%20the%20driveway%20and%20a%20cluster%20of%20RVs%2C%20owned%20by%20her%20six%20tenants%2C%20in%20a%20forested%20glade%20beside%20a%20creek.%20Other%20residents%20include%20Cooley%2C%20Fern%20and%20Cooley's%209-year-old%20son%2C%20Diego%2C%20two%20cats%2C%20and%2C%20the%20day%20I%20was%20there%2C%20a%20fat%20yellow%20labrador%20who'd%20showed%20up%20out%20of%20nowhere%20and%20would%20not%20go%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20necessarily%20a%20commune%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Cooley%2C%20who%20is%20wearing%20a%20hemp%20bracelet%20and%20a%20novelty%20Star%20Wars%20T-shirt%20that%20says%20%26quot%3Bthe%20Dadalorian.%26quot%3B%20It's%20%26quot%3Bliving%20more%20communally%2C%26quot%3B%20Fern%20said%2C%20finishing%20his%20sentence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20being%20Fern's%20ex-husband%2C%20Cooley%20is%20the%20father%20of%20her%20child%2C%20her%20roommate%2C%20and%20the%20coauthor%20of%20the%20%26quot%3BPolysecure%26quot%3B%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3E2023%20follow-up%2C%20%26quot%3BPolywise%3A%20A%20Deeper%20Dive%20into%20Navigating%20Open%20Relationships.%26quot%3B%20Cooley%20has%20his%20own%20bedroom%20downstairs%20with%20a%20kitchenette%2C%20but%20they%20usually%20have%20breakfast%20together%20upstairs%20and%20%26quot%3Bjust%20chat%2C%26quot%3B%20Fern%20said%2C%20mostly%20about%20work%20%E2%80%94%20they're%20currently%20cowriting%20a%20new%20book%20on%20shame.%20Though%20Cooley%20and%20Fern%20disentangled%20from%20a%20%26quot%3Bprimary%20emotional%20attachment%26quot%3B%20when%20they%20divorced%2C%20what%20they%20have%20now%20is%20%26quot%3Bno%20less%20meaningful%2C%26quot%3B%20Cooley%20said%20as%20the%20three%20of%20us%20sat%20down%20together%20on%20the%20front%20porch.%20%26quot%3BHe%20calls%20us%20life%20partners%2C%26quot%3B%20Fern%20added.%20%26quot%3BI%20like%20that%20phrase.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPart%20of%20Fern%20and%20Cooley's%20journey%20to%20polyamory%20came%20from%20a%20desire%20to%20have%20kids%20outside%20the%20%26quot%3Bdisaster%20of%20a%20nuclear-family%20framework%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20Fern%20put%20it.%20(Fern%20defines%20polyamory%20as%20a%20subset%20of%20consensual%20nomonogamy%20that%20prioritizes%20emotional%20intimacy%2C%20though%20it's%20often%20used%20as%20a%20catch-all%20term.)%20They%20both%20have%20primary%20partners%20with%20kids%20of%20their%20own.%20Cooley's%20girlfriend%2C%20Julia%2C%20lives%20in%20an%20%26quot%3Bintentional%20community%26quot%3B%20called%20Earth%20Haven%20Ecovillage%2C%20about%20an%20hour%20away%2C%20where%20residents%20live%20and%20tend%20the%20land%20communally.%20John%2C%20the%20boyfriend%20Fern%20met%20on%20Feeld%2C%20lives%20about%2090%20minutes%20away%20and%20shares%20custody%20of%20his%20two%20kids%20with%20his%20now%20ex-wife.%20Fern%20sees%20her%20partner%20two%20to%20three%20times%20a%20week%2C%20and%20she%20and%20Cooley%20alternate%20Fridays%20and%20Saturdays%20for%20date%20night.%20Everyone%20helps%20out%20with%20parenting%3A%20Julia%20recently%20brought%20her%2012-year-old%20daughter%20over%20to%20do%20crafts%20with%20Fern's%20mom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221584%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22white%20lotus%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F646b39c063c86a0018cd141d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221056%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIn%20the%20hit%20show%20%26quot%3BThe%20White%20Lotus%2C%26quot%3B%20two%20young%20couples%20test%20the%20limits%20of%20monogamy.%20%3Cp%3EHBO%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFern%20and%20Cooley%20seem%20like%20people%20who%20have%20spent%20a%20lot%20of%20time%20meditating%2C%20processing%2C%20resolving%2C%20and%20therapizing.%20Fern's%2067-year-old%20mother%2C%20Apryl%2C%20who%20lives%20with%20them%20for%20the%20majority%20of%20the%20year%2C%20operates%20at%20a%20decidedly%20less%20laid-back%20frequency.%20The%20morning%20I'm%20there%2C%20she%20is%20in%20the%20midst%20of%20a%20cleaning%20frenzy.%20She%20bursts%20onto%20the%20deck%20in%20floral%20pajama%20pants%20and%20flip-flops%2C%20a%20pile%20of%20frizzy%20gray%20curls%20escaping%20from%20a%20hairclip%2C%20and%20flops%20down%20next%20to%20her%20daughter%20on%20the%20couch.%20While%20raising%20Fern%20in%20public%20housing%20in%20Sheepshead%20Bay%2C%20Brooklyn%2C%20Apryl%20had%20relationships%20with%20multiple%20men%20who%20were%20in%20and%20out%20of%20her%20life.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20very%20rare%20that%20I%20broke%20up%20with%20a%20boyfriend%20but%20I%20didn't%20ever%20see%20them%20again%2C%26quot%3B%20Apryl%20said%20as%20she%20leaned%20forward%20to%20scrub%20a%20stain%20on%20the%20coffee%20table.%20%26quot%3BI%20just%20never%20wanted%20to%20let%20go%20of%20somebody.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20whiplash%20was%20stressful%20for%20Fern%2C%20who%20was%20also%20brought%20up%20by%20her%20father%2C%20an%20alcoholic%2C%20and%20her%20stepmom%2C%20who%20had%20a%20severe%20mental%20illness.%20It%20shaped%20both%20her%20early%20%26quot%3Bdisorganized%26quot%3B%20attachment%20style%20and%20her%20eventual%20philosophy%20around%20relationships.%20Her%20mom's%20exes%20largely%20remained%20important%20figures%20in%20Fern's%20life.%20%26quot%3BYou%20really%20set%20Jessica%20up%20for%20a%20nervous%20system%20that%20was%20normalizing%20people%20coming%20in%20and%20a%20certain%20kind%20of%20fluidity%20of%20attachment%2C%26quot%3B%20Cooley%20said%20in%20a%20soft-spoken%20Southern%20drawl%20well-suited%20to%20his%20work%20in%20nonviolent%20communication.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Fern%20and%20Cooley%20came%20out%20to%20Apryl%20as%20polyamorous%2C%20she%20didn't%20bat%20an%20eye.%20%26quot%3BMaybe%20that%20would%20have%20worked%20for%20me!%26quot%3B%20Apryl%20said%2C%20slapping%20her%20knee%20and%20laughing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAttachment%20theory%2C%20which%20is%20the%20basis%20of%20%26quot%3BPolysecure%2C%26quot%3B%20was%20conceived%20in%20the%201950s%20by%20the%20British%20psychoanalyst%20John%20Bowlby.%20He%20argued%20that%20the%20relationships%20we%20develop%20with%20our%20early%20caregivers%20go%20on%20to%20influence%20all%20of%20our%20emotional%20bonds%2C%20or%20%26quot%3Battachments.%26quot%3B%20In%20the%201970s%2C%20a%20psychologist%20named%20Mary%20Ainsworth%20built%20on%20Bowlby's%20research%20to%20define%20different%20types%20of%20attachment%20styles%20people%20can%20have.%20Nowadays%2C%20it's%20widely%20accepted%20that%20there%20are%20four%20main%20types%20of%20attachment%3A%20secure%2C%20anxious%2C%20avoidant%2C%20and%20disorganized.%20Researchers%20estimate%20that%2050%25%20of%20people%20are%20securely%20attached%2C%20meaning%20they%20easily%20feel%20stable%20and%20safe%20in%20relationships.%20The%20rest%20of%20us%20are%20insecure.%20In%20the%20simplest%20terms%2C%20those%20who%20are%20primarily%20anxious%20fear%20abandonment%20and%20cling%20tighter%20when%20they%20feel%20distance%3B%20avoidant%20people%20fear%20being%20smothered%20and%20pull%20away%20at%20signs%20of%20intimacy%3B%20and%20disorganized%20people%20are%20a%20mix%20of%20both.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFern's%20central%20argument%20is%20that%20just%20as%20kids%20can%20have%20secure%20attachments%20to%20multiple%20caregivers%2C%20it's%20possible%20for%20adults%20to%20have%20secure%20attachments%20with%20multiple%20partners.%20%26quot%3BSecure%20attachment%20is%20an%20embodied%20expression%20built%20upon%20how%20we%20consistently%20respond%20and%20attune%20to%20each%20other%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20writes%2C%20%26quot%3Bnot%20something%20that%20gets%20created%20through%20structure%20and%20hierarchy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%20the%20transition%20to%20nonmonogamy%20requires%20an%20immense%20paradigm%20shift%20and%20can%20trigger%20fears%20that%20feel%20unmanageable.%20As%20Fern%20writes%20in%20%26quot%3BPolysecure%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20wasn't%20uncommon%20for%20her%20partnered%20clients%20to%20say%20they%20%26quot%3Btheoretically%20want%20to%20be%20poly%2C%20but%20emotionally%20they%20don't%20know%20if%20they%20can%20do%20it.%26quot%3B%20The%20book%20proposes%20coping%20techniques%20for%20poly%20newbies%20including%20creating%20bedtime%20or%20waking%20rituals%20with%20each%20partner%2C%20expressing%20gratitude%20regularly%2C%20and%20not%20fighting%20over%20text.%20One%20of%20Fern's%20polyamorous%20colleagues%2C%20she%20writes%2C%20%26quot%3Bknows%20the%20love%20languages%20of%20each%20of%20his%20different%20partners%26quot%3B%20(referring%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fsex-relationships%2Flove-languages%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Epopular%20pop-psychology%20theory%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E)%20and%20makes%20sure%20to%20lavish%20them%20with%20the%20gifts%2C%20acts%20of%20service%2C%20or%20physical%20touch%20after%20spending%20time%20apart.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPolysecure%2C%26quot%3B%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Eand%20even%20more%20so%20%26quot%3BPolywise%2C%26quot%3B%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Eborrows%20a%20lot%20of%20ideas%20from%20more%20fringe%20therapeutic%20modalities%20like%20polyvagal%20theory%2C%20which%20emphasizes%20the%20importance%20of%20the%20nervous%20system%20in%20regulating%20social%20behavior.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EAs%20Fern%20writes%2C%20the%20stress%20response%20humans%20evolved%20to%20flee%20from%20wild%20animals%20now%20gets%20activated%20by%20%26quot%3Byour%20partner%20on%20the%20couch%20texting%20with%20someone%20else%20or%20your%20date%20being%2020%20minutes%20late.%26quot%3B%20When%20you're%20juggling%20multiple%20relationships%2C%20trigger%20management%20%E2%80%94%20which%20can%20range%20from%20cognitive%20reframing%20to%20deep-belly%20breathing%20%E2%80%94%20becomes%20even%20more%20essential.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20whole%20metaphor%20of%20falling%20in%20love%20frames%20it%20as%20an%20accidental%20occurrence%20where%20there's%20no%20choice%2C%26quot%3B%20Cooley%20said.%20Their%20goal%20is%20to%20give%20people%20%26quot%3Ba%20sense%20of%20agency%20around%20how%20their%20nervous%20system%20shows%20up%20in%20relationships.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhich%20all%20sound%20great%2C%20in%20theory.%20Jealous%3F%20Journal%20about%20it!%20Heartbroken%3F%20Do%20a%20breathing%20exercise!%20But%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20managing%20the%20really%20heady%20stuff%2C%20these%20strategies%20start%20to%20feel%20a%20little%20inadequate.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20obvious%20she%20was%20naturally%20'wired'%20for%20poly%20relationships%2C%26quot%3B%20wrote%20one%20online%20commenter%20of%20Fern%2C%20summarizing%20a%20common%20critique.%20%26quot%3BShe%20speaks%20of%20jealousy%20in%20a%20very%20abstract%20and%20disconnected%20way%20that%20leads%20me%20to%20believe%20she%20has%20never%20felt%20it%20in%20her%20life.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhich%20isn't%20quite%20fair%3B%20Fern%20does%20get%20jealous.%20In%20particular%2C%20she%20has%20a%20deep%20fear%20of%20being%20lied%20to%20by%20a%20partner%2C%20although%2C%20she%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BAs%20far%20as%20I%20know%2C%20I've%20never%20been%20cheated%20on.%26quot%3B%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EBut%20she's%20learned%20what%20she%20needs%20to%20tolerate%20this%20insecurity%20%E2%80%94%20namely%2C%20a%20lot%20of%20positive%20reinforcement%20and%20plenty%20of%20transparency.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20like%2C%20it's%20OK%20if%20you%20tell%20me%20you're%20interested%20in%20someone.%20It's%20totally%20allowed.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Jessica%20Fern%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66d8643214a5cd1fcc8d00e7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFern%20has%20been%20drawn%20to%20psychoanalysis%20since%20she%20was%20a%20class%20mediator%20in%20elementary%20school.%20%3Cp%3EMike%20Belleme%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lesson%20in%20%26quot%3BPolysecure%26quot%3B%20is%20that%20every%20dynamic%20is%20different%2C%20and%20the%20important%20thing%20is%20finding%20what%20works%20for%20you.%20She%20sees%20it%20kind%20of%20like%20a%20sport%20%26quot%3Bwhere%20some%20people%20just%20naturally%20have%20a%20talent%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20%26quot%3Bthat%20talent%20can%20also%20be%20cultivated.%26quot%3B%20She%20knows%20that%20not%20everyone%20can%20handle%20the%20emotional%20strain%20of%20multiple%20relationships%20or%20the%20immense%20amount%20of%20time%20and%20logistics%20they%20require.%20After%20tallying%20up%20the%20many%20daily%20stressors%20of%20life%20%E2%80%94%20work%2C%20childcare%2C%20self-care%2C%20financial%20obligations%2C%20and%20so%20on%20%E2%80%94%20she%20writes%20that%20she%20is%20%26quot%3Bactually%20surprised%20anyone%20has%20time%20for%20even%20one%20securely%20attached%20relationship.%26quot%3B%20Reading%20%26quot%3BPolysecure%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20can%20be%20hard%20not%20to%20come%20away%20feeling%20like%20polysecurity%20is%20less%20an%20attainable%20goal%20than%20a%20fantasy%20for%20only%20the%20most%20annoyingly%20well-adjusted.%20I'm%20reminded%20of%20Tobias%20and%20Lindsay%20in%20%26quot%3BArrested%20Development%26quot%3B%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Edeciding%20to%20open%20their%20marriage%3A%20%26quot%3BDid%20it%20work%20for%20those%20people%3F%26quot%3B%20Lindsay%20asks%20of%20Tobias'%20clients.%20%26quot%3BNo%2C%20it%20never%20does.%20I%20mean%20these%20people%20somehow%20delude%20themselves%20into%20thinking%20it%20might%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20responds.%20%26quot%3BBut%20it%20might%20work%20for%20%3Cem%3Eus%3C%2Fem%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20biggest%20questions%20levied%20by%20critics%20of%20consensual%20nonmonogamy%20is%2C%20basically%2C%20who%20has%20the%20time%20and%20energy%20for%20all%20this%3F%20Are%20the%20only%20people%20who%20can%20swing%20it%20rich%20white%20women%20like%20Molly%20Roden%20Winter%2C%20who%20can%20afford%20nannies%20and%20expensive%20therapy%20sessions%3F%20It's%20true%20that%20the%20lifestyle%20seems%20to%20involve%20an%20awful%20lot%20of%20homework%2C%20not%20to%20mention%20an%20SAT's%20worth%20of%20vocabulary%3A%20metamour%2C%20the%20lover%20of%20one's%20lover%3B%20compersion%2C%20the%20happiness%20one%20feels%20seeing%20their%20partner%20happy%20with%20someone%20else%3B%20and%20NRE%2C%20intoxicating%20%26quot%3Bnew%20relationship%20energy.%26quot%3B%20There's%20a%20superior%20tone%20to%20a%20lot%20of%20nonmonogamy%20discourse%20that%20understandably%20pisses%20people%20off%3B%20nobody%20wants%20to%20hear%20a%20lecture%20on%20the%20moral%20virtues%20of%20veganism%20while%20they're%20eating%20a%20burger.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%20Fern's%20not%20saying%20that%20you're%20a%20failure%20if%20you%20don't%20have%20three%20boyfriends%3B%20she's%20just%20trying%20to%20remind%20people%20that%20they%20have%20agency%20in%20how%20they%20structure%20their%20romantic%2C%20familial%2C%20and%20sexual%20lives.%20She%20also%20says%20that%20while%20stories%20like%20Winter's%20tend%20to%20get%20more%20airtime%2C%20she%20has%20clients%20from%20all%20backgrounds%20who%20are%20making%20the%20nonmonogamy%20thing%20work.%20What's%20more%2C%20%26quot%3Beven%20in%20exclusive%20relationships%20it's%20like%2C%20of%20course%2C%20you%20have%20to%20put%20in%20effort%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20For%20instance%2C%20you%20wouldn't%20complain%20that%20you%20bought%20a%20car%20and%20have%20to%20put%20gas%20in%2C%20Fern%20said%2C%20before%20stopping%20to%20correct%20herself%20%E2%80%94%20she%20recently%20bought%20a%20new%20Tesla%2C%20a%20gift%20to%20herself%2C%20with%20the%20royalties%20from%20%26quot%3BPolysecure.%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BWell%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20nodding%20to%20her%20new%20whip%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20have%20to%20put%20gas%20in%20this%20car.%26quot%3B%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EFern%20has%20been%20psychoanalyzing%20people%20since%20signing%20up%20to%20be%20a%20class%20mediator%20in%20elementary%20school.%20In%20college%20at%20SUNY%20Purchase%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20always%20used%20to%20describe%20her%20as%20the%20Dear%20Abby%20of%20her%20friends%2C%26quot%3B%20Apryl%20added.%20%26quot%3BShe%20literally%20moved%20out%20of%20the%20dorm%20because%20of%20the%20pressure%20of%20everybody%20wanting%20to%20come%20into%20her%20room%20and%20being%20like%3A%20I%20need%20your%20help!%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20spent%20much%20of%20her%20early%2020s%20exploring%20various%20therapeutic%20techniques%2C%20including%20massage%20therapy%20and%20something%20called%20eye%20movement%20desensitization%20and%20reprocessing%20(EMDR)%20therapy%2C%20to%20try%20to%20unravel%20her%20childhood.%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20determined%20that%20though%20this%20always%20will%20be%20a%20part%20of%20me%2C%20it%20doesn't%20have%20to%20control%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFern%20had%20dated%20women%2C%20fooled%20around%20with%20group%20stuff%20in%20college%2C%20and%20had%20multiple%20casual%20relationships%20simultaneously%2C%20but%20she'd%20never%20thought%20too%20much%20about%20it.%20She%20met%20Cooley%20in%202002%20at%20massage%20school%2C%20and%20after%20years%20of%20friendship%2C%20they%20started%20dating%20exclusively%20in%202008%20and%20got%20on%20what's%20known%20in%20polyworld%20as%20%26quot%3Bthe%20relationship%20escalator%26quot%3B%3A%20moved%20in%2C%20got%20hitched%2C%20got%20pregnant.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20big%20shift%20happened%20once%20she%20had%20her%20son%2C%20during%20what%20she%20called%20her%20%26quot%3Bfirst%20mommy%20meltdown.%26quot%3B%20She%20remembers%20one%20day%20when%20Cooley%20had%20gone%20back%20to%20work%20and%20she%20was%20running%20on%20no%20sleep%2C%20rocking%20a%20screaming%20Diego%2C%20and%20feeling%20profoundly%20isolated%20and%20adrift.%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20like%2C%20I%20can't%20do%20this.%20I%20have%20to%20be%20his%20mother%20and%20his%20food%20and%20his%20entertainment%20and%20his%20playmate%2C%20and%20I%20can't%20be%20everything%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BOne%20partner%20is%20now%20what%20we%20used%20to%20get%20from%20a%20whole%20village.%20I'm%20like%2C%20how%20is%20one%20human%20supposed%20to%20be%20the%20whole%20thing%20this%20child's%20nervous%20system%20needs%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPolyamory%20may%20still%20be%20fringe%2C%20but%20mainstream%20mental-health%20and%20relationship%20experts%20are%20increasingly%20making%20the%20argument%20that%20monogamy%20isn't%20our%20default%20state.%20The%202010%20bestseller%20%26quot%3BSex%20at%20Dawn%26quot%3B%20argues%20that%20monogamous%20coupledom%20is%20a%20relatively%20recent%20evolution%20and%20that%20we%20used%20to%20raise%20kids%20much%20more%20communally.%20And%20while%20the%20book's%20methodology%20and%20conclusions%20have%20been%20heavily%20criticized%20for%20relying%20on%20flimsy%20historical%20evidence%2C%20its%20ideas%20have%20stuck%20around.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20CEO%20of%20the%20poly-dating%20app%20Feeld%20told%20Axios%20they'd%20seen%20a%20500%25%20increase%20in%20users%20identifying%20as%20polyamorous%20or%20ethically%20nonmonogamous%20over%20the%20past%20three%20years%2C%20while%20a%202016%20study%20from%20the%20Kinsey%20Institute%20suggested%20that%20one%20in%20five%20Americans%20have%20been%20in%20some%20sort%20of%20consensually%20nonmonogamous%20dynamic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20a%20number%20of%20explanations%20for%20why%20that%20is%20the%20case.%20One%20is%20the%20pandemic%2C%20when%20people%20trapped%20indoors%20for%20months%20started%20to%20rethink%20pretty%20much%20everything%2C%20including%20sex%20and%20relationships.%20Christopher%20Gleason%2C%20the%20author%20of%202023's%20%26quot%3BAmerican%20Poly%2C%26quot%3B%20thinks%20another%20huge%20factor%20is%20the%20increased%20acceptance%20of%20bisexuality%20as%20queer%20culture%20becomes%20more%20mainstream.%20(%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC5958351%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DWhen%2520analyzing%2520the%2520whole%2520sample%2Cheterosexual%2520participants%252C%252014%2525%2520of%2520gay%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ENational%20survey%20data%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20shows%20LGBTQ%2B%20relationships%20are%20much%20more%20likely%20to%20be%20nonmonogamous%20than%20straight%20ones.)%20For%20many%20people%2C%20the%20gateway%20into%20ethical%20nonmonogamy%20is%20a%20hetero%20relationship%20where%20one%20partner%20says%20they'd%20%26quot%3Blike%20to%20explore%26quot%3B%20sexually%20with%20a%20different%20gender.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20how%20I%20did%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Gleason%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFern%20sees%20her%20work%20as%20part%20of%20a%20larger%20progressive%20struggle.%20We've%20had%20%26quot%3Bthe%20civil-rights%20movement%2C%20then%20the%20sexual%20revolution%2C%20and%20then%20we%20sort%20of%20had%20queer%20rights%2C%20and%20now%20we%20have%20the%20gender%20binary%20being%20deconstructed%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Fern.%20%26quot%3BMonogamy's%20kind%20of%20the%20last%20thing%20to%20deconstruct.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fplatform.twitter.com%2Fwidgets.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22twitter%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3Ei%20hope%20they're%20doing%20okay%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2F83N3Mruqse%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2F83N3Mruqse%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%E2%80%94%20seraph%20(%40despaird0ll)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fdespaird0ll%2Fstatus%2F1770142471097331737%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EMarch%2019%2C%202024%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20Diego's%20birth%20in%202014%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EFern%20was%20questioning%20concepts%20around%20motherhood%20and%20the%20nuclear%20family.%20She%20had%20completed%20her%20master's%20degree%20in%20conflict%20resolution%20at%20George%20Mason%20University%20and%20started%20working%20as%20a%20psychotherapist%20in%20Boulder%2C%20Colorado%2C%20the%20following%20year.%20She%20was%20also%20hearing%20more%20and%20more%20of%20her%20clients%20talk%20about%20their%20open%20relationships.%20Some%20were%20seeking%20sexual%20exploration%20because%20their%20erotic%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eneeds%20weren't%20aligned%20with%20those%20of%20a%20spouse%3B%20others%20saw%20it%20as%20a%20tool%20of%20personal%20growth%20and%20discovery.%20Fern%20herself%20always%20had%20immense%20bandwidth%20for%20talking%20and%20thinking%20about%20people%20and%20relationships%20the%20way%20others%20might%20be%20drawn%20to%20politics%20or%20playing%20the%20cello.%20She%20goes%20deep%20with%20people%3B%20she%20doesn't%20do%20casual%20friendships%2C%20and%20she%20doesn't%20do%20one-night%20stands.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20there%20probably%20is%20something%20to%20the%20idea%20that%20polyamorous%20people%20are%20more%20drawn%20to%20this%20revelational%20psychological%20realm%26quot%3B%20where%20managing%20complex%20interpersonal%20dynamics%20%26quot%3Bdoesn't%20feel%20like%20too%20much%2C%20even%20if%20it%20is%20too%20much%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BWhereas%20if%20I%20walked%20into%20my%20mom's%20craft%20shop%2C%20I%20get%20overwhelmed%2C%20like%2C%20what%20the%20fuck%20is%20all%20this%20shit%3F%26quot%3B%20In%20the%20next%20few%20months%2C%20she%20devoured%20every%20book%20she%20could%20find%20on%20the%20topic%2C%20and%20she%20and%20Cooley%20decided%20to%20give%20it%20a%20go.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20as%20Fern%20and%20Cooley%20found%2C%20no%20books%20could%20have%20prepared%20them%20for%20how%20hard%20it%20actually%20was.%20The%20first%20few%20weeks%20after%20opening%20up%2C%20Cooley%20felt%20what%20he%20describes%20in%20%26quot%3BPolywise%26quot%3B%20as%20%26quot%3Bsearing%20anguish.%26quot%3B%20As%20soon%20as%20sex%20came%20into%20play%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20became%20a%20fucking%20lunatic%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BMy%20identity%20as%20a%20more%20'evolved'%20or%20'conscious'%20man%20started%20to%20unravel%20as%20I%20found%20myself%20measuring%20my%20own%20self-worth%20in%20terms%20of%20how%20often%20she%20and%20I%20were%20having%20sex%26quot%3B%20and%20wondering%20if%20her%20other%20partners%20had%20a%20%26quot%3Bbigger%20cock.%26quot%3B%20Mostly%2C%20it%20just%20felt%20like%20the%20walls%20were%20caving%20in.%20In%202019%2C%20they%20filed%20for%20divorce.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20most%20couples%2C%20that%20would%20have%20been%20it%3A%20a%20two-decade-long%20relationship%20reduced%20to%20curt%20nods%20at%20school%20drop-offs.%20But%20if%20typical%20relationships%20are%20an%20escalator%2C%20Fern%20and%20Cooley%20were%20on%20something%20closer%20to%20an%20M.C.%20Escher%20staircase.%20After%20they%20split%2C%20Cooley%20went%20on%20his%20own%20journey%2C%20which%20included%20ayahuasca-%20and%20MDMA-assisted%20psychotherapy%2C%20EMDR%2C%20somatic%20therapy%2C%20talk%20therapy%2C%20men's%20groups%2C%20and%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Esome%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ekink%2C%20to%20try%20to%20figure%20out%20why%20opening%20their%20relationship%20had%20triggered%20so%20much%20anxiety%20and%20fear%20of%20abandonment.%20Gradually%2C%20the%20pair%20began%20to%20reconnect%2C%20albeit%20non-romantically%2C%20to%20find%20a%20way%20to%20raise%20their%20son%20together.%20And%20Fern%20set%20about%20turning%20her%20failed%20marriage%20into%20a%20book.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20late%202010s%2C%20the%20poly%20publishing%20world%20was%20experiencing%20a%20drought.%20It%20had%20been%20two%20decades%20since%20%26quot%3BThe%20Ethical%20Slut%26quot%3B%20was%20published%3B%20Franklin%20Veaux%20and%20Eve%20Rickert's%20%26quot%3BMore%20Than%20Two%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20came%20out%20in%202014%2C%20had%20an%20asterisk%20beside%20it%20after%20multiple%20women%2C%20including%20Rickert%2C%20accused%20Veaux%20of%20manipulative%20and%20controlling%20behavior%20(Veaux%20dismissed%20it%20as%20a%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fblog.franklinveaux.com%2F2024%2F05%2Fstalking-harassment-and-the-north-american-polyamory-scene%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esmear%20campaign%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B).%20In%202019%2C%20Rickert%20heard%20Fern%20give%20a%20talk%20on%20consensual%20nonmonogamy.%20By%20that%20point%2C%20Rickert%20was%20running%20her%20own%20publishing%20company%20focused%20on%20sex%20and%20relationships.%20She%20had%20long%20been%20looking%20for%20a%20book%20that%20reimagined%20attachment%20theory%20for%20nonmonogamy%20in%20an%20accessible%20way%20and%20convinced%20Fern%20to%20turn%20her%20talk%20into%20a%20book.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20%26quot%3BPolysecure%26quot%3B%20came%20out%20mid-pandemic%2C%20it%20was%20a%20%26quot%3Bphenomenon%26quot%3B%20beyond%20anything%20Rickert's%20small%20Vancouver%20Island%20publishing%20house%20had%20ever%20experienced%2C%20Rickert%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFern%20said%20she%20now%20has%20hundreds%20of%20people%20on%20the%20waiting%20list%20for%20her%20psychotherapy%20practice.%20She%20currently%20sees%20more%20than%2060%20clients%2C%20almost%20all%20of%20them%20queer%20or%20in%20%26quot%3Bnontraditional%26quot%3B%20relationships.%20Hearing%20her%20talk%20about%20her%20clients%20is%20like%20hearing%20a%20chemist%20describe%20molecular%20formulas%3A%20a%20lot%20of%20triads%2C%20a%20V%20(one%20woman%20and%20her%20two%20partners%20who%20aren't%20together)%2C%20and%20a%20polycule%20of%20almost%20a%20dozen%20people.%20A%20lot%20of%20clients%20are%20couples%20trying%20to%20open%20up%3B%20a%20few%20are%20navigating%20cheating.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20really%20hard%20if%20the%20person's%20still%20dating%20the%20person%20they%20cheated%20on%2C%26quot%3B%20Fern%20said.%20Fern%20has%20little%20patience%20for%20the%20growing%20number%20of%20people%20(usually%20straight%2C%20cisgender%20men)%20on%20dating%20apps%20calling%20themselves%20%26quot%3Bethically%20nonmonogamous%26quot%3B%20to%20avoid%20commitment.%20%26quot%3BAnything%20can%20be%20misused%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20some%20say%20the%20book%20has%20been%20transformative%2C%20for%20others%2C%20applying%20Fern's%20teachings%20in%20the%20real%20world%20has%20been%20more%20fraught.%20One%20Brooklyn%20contractor%20in%20his%2040s%20said%20he%20started%20experiencing%20panic%20attacks%20and%20suicidal%20thoughts%20after%20opening%20up%20his%20marriage%20in%202020.%20Dating%20felt%20like%20an%20exhausting%2C%20hedonic%20treadmill%2C%20in%20which%20he%20was%20constantly%20hunting%20for%20a%20new%20dopamine%20rush.%20Eventually%2C%20he%20and%20his%20wife%20decided%20to%20return%20to%20monogamy%2C%20though%20they%20still%20haven't%20fully%20unpacked%20what%20they%20went%20through.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20kind%20of%20like%20we%20traumatized%20each%20other%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20After%20that%2C%20they%20took%20all%20the%20polyamory%20books%20they'd%20read%3Cem%3E%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3Eincluding%20%26quot%3BPolysecure%2C%26quot%3B%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Eand%20threw%20them%20in%20a%20bonfire%20at%20their%20Catskills%20cabin.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20just%20the%20blind%20leading%20the%20blind%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey%20talk%20about%20things%20and%20concepts%20that%20make%20sense%2C%20but%20none%20of%20these%20people%20have%20successful%20relationships.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDavis%2C%20the%20New%20York%20Magazine%20writer%2C%20started%20exploring%20polyamory%20during%20COVID%20and%20eventually%20found%20herself%20in%20a%20%26quot%3Bnonhierarchical%26quot%3B%20relationship%20with%20a%20man%20who%20also%20had%20another%20partner.%20In%20so-called%20hierarchical%20polyamory%2C%20some%20partners%20take%20priority%2C%20the%20way%20a%20couple%20in%20an%20open%20marriage%20might%20put%20each%20other's%20needs%20before%20those%20of%20their%20secondary%20partners.%20A%20less-hierarchical%20%26quot%3Brelationship%20anarchy%26quot%3B%20approach%20puts%20everyone%20on%20a%20more%20even%20playing%20field.%20Yet%20Davis%20grew%20frustrated%20by%20the%20way%20her%20partner%20used%20his%20attachment%20style%20as%20an%20excuse%2C%20such%20as%20when%20he%20neglected%20to%20tell%20her%20he'd%20planned%20a%20trip%20to%20the%20Bahamas%20with%20his%20other%20partner%20on%20their%20anniversary.%20%26quot%3BHe%20was%20like%2C%20I%20just%20can't%20help%20it%20because%20I'm%20avoidant!%26quot%3B%20She%20also%20found%20that%20Fern's%20perspective%20as%20a%20white%20woman%20in%20a%20long-term%20relationship%20didn't%20gel%20with%20her%20experience%20as%20a%20woman%20of%20color%20practicing%20polyamory%20on%20her%20own.%20%26quot%3BFrom%20now%20on%2C%20I'm%20just%20going%20to%20have%20a%20partner%20and%20then%20be%20like%2C%20'Hey%2C%20guess%20what%3F%20I'm%20going%20to%20cheat%20on%20you%20this%20month.%20Is%20that%20cool%3F'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222048%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Jessica%20Fern%20and%20her%20boyfriend%20John%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66d777811d8d2deb96b86cb9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221536%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJohn's%20profile%20on%20Feeld%20advertised%20his%20services%20as%20an%20%26quot%3Bexperienced%20bull%20for%20hot%20wives%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20often%20involved%20having%20sex%20with%20women%20whose%20husbands%20watched.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20John%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20definitely%20people%20out%20there%20doing%20open%20relationships%20well%20%E2%80%94%20they%20just%20might%20not%20be%20the%20people%20reading%2C%20writing%2C%20or%20Redditing%20about%20it%20the%20most.%20The%20two%20people%20I%20know%20in%20the%20most%20successful%2C%20relaxed%20nonmonogamous%20situations%20are%20bisexual%20women%20in%20long-term%20hetero%20relationships%20(which%20might%20not%20be%20a%20coincidence%20%E2%80%94%20as%20one%20put%20it%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20bis%20do%20it%20better%26quot%3B).%20They%20both%20date%20women%20on%20the%20side.%20Neither%20has%20ever%20read%20anything%20about%20the%20subject.%20%26quot%3BNo%2C%20we're%20just%20that%20good.%20Lol%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20other%20texted%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Brooklyn%20writer%20Daniel%20Lavery%2C%20who%20has%20spoken%20extensively%20about%20living%20and%20parenting%20as%20a%20throuple%2C%20shared%20a%20similar%20sentiment.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20think%20any%20of%20us%20have%20read%20any%20books%20on%20polyamory%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20though%20it's%20not%20that%20their%20household%20is%20%26quot%3Banti-book.%26quot%3B%20Lavery%20said%20they%20really%20liked%20%26quot%3BThe%20Happiest%20Baby%20on%20the%20Block.%26quot%3B%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20day%20started%20to%20cool%2C%20Fern%20and%20I%20said%20goodbye%20to%20Diego%2C%20Apryl%2C%20Cooley%2C%20their%20cats%2C%20and%20someone%20else's%20dog%2C%20and%20drove%20into%20Asheville%20for%20a%20stroll.%20After%20pointing%20out%20some%20local%20landmarks%20%E2%80%94%20the%20French%20Broad%20River%20winding%20through%20the%20city%20and%20Gray%20Eagle%20concert%20hall%2C%20where%20she%20was%20a%20panelist%20at%20an%20event%20called%20%26quot%3BVino%20and%20Vulvas%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20we%20stopped%20at%20her%20favorite%20gift%20shop.%20She%20picked%20up%20a%20%26quot%3BKinky%20Truth%20or%20Dare%26quot%3B%20game%2C%20and%20we%20read%20a%20few%20questions%20before%20it%20became%20clear%20we%20weren't%20the%20target%20demographic.%20%26quot%3B'Have%20you%20ever%20experimented%20with%20the%20same%20sex%3F'%20Lame%20question%2C%26quot%3B%20Fern%20said%2C%20returning%20it%20to%20the%20shelf.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESomething%20else%20caught%20Fern's%20eye%3A%20a%20brown%20candle%20shaped%20like%20a%20girthy%20penis%20with%20a%20label%20saying%20%26quot%3Bburn%20the%20patriarchy.%26quot%3B%20When%20Cooley's%20girlfriend%2C%20Julia%2C%20got%20her%20divorce%20papers%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20got%20her%20this%2C%26quot%3B%20Fern%20said%2C%20brandishing%20it%20excitedly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThings%20are%20in%20a%20good%20place%20now%2C%20but%20Fern's%20journey%20to%20polysecurity%20hasn't%20been%20all%20sunshine%20and%20roses%20and%20novelty%20dick%20candles.%20She's%20been%20in%20about%20six%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eserious%20relationships%20since%20opening%20up%2C%20and%20while%20she's%20learned%20something%20from%20all%20of%20them%2C%20her%20most%20recent%20breakup%20was%20by%20far%20the%20ugliest.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EIn%20early%202020%2C%20two%20years%20before%20she%20met%20John%20on%20Feeld%2C%20Fern%20was%20in%20a%20relationship%20with%20a%20man%20she%20thought%20she'd%20be%20with%20forever%20(she%20asked%20me%20not%20to%20include%20his%20name).%20Fern%20and%20Cooley%20were%20in%20a%20comfortable%20co-parenting%20groove%20and%20when%20the%20pandemic%20hit%2C%20the%20three%20of%20them%20made%20the%20%26quot%3Bradical%20decision%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20Cooley%20put%20it%2C%20to%20move%20to%20an%20eco-village%20in%20Costa%20Rica%20together.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20a%20while%2C%20things%20were%20copacetic.%20They%20lived%20in%20a%20bamboo%20house%2C%20and%20Diego%20attended%20school%20outdoors.%20Surprisingly%2C%20the%20hardest%20thing%20to%20explain%20to%20their%20community%20of%20ex-pats%20was%20that%20they%20weren't%20all%20fucking.%20%26quot%3BAlmost%20everyone%20had%20some%20idea%20that%20the%20three%20of%20us%20were%20in%20some%20kind%20of%20polysexual%20triad%2C%26quot%3B%20Cooley%20said.%20In%202021%2C%20the%20trio%20decided%20to%20move%20back%20to%20the%20States.%20Fern%20and%20Cooley%20wanted%20to%20raise%20their%20son%20in%20a%20progressive%20city%20close%20to%20nature%20but%20insulated%20from%20natural%20disasters%20%E2%80%94%20%26quot%3Bhurricanes%2C%20earthquakes%2C%20fires%2C%20and%20tornados%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20and%20Asheville%20fit%20the%20bill.%20Fern%2C%20Cooley%2C%20and%20Fern's%20partner%20bought%20the%20property%20together%20and%20settled%20in%2C%20planning%20to%20live%20there%20long%20term.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20then%20a%20different%20kind%20of%20natural%20disaster%20hit%3A%20Fern's%20partner%20was%20increasingly%20struggling%20to%20manage%20his%20temper%20and%20erupting%20into%20angry%20outbursts%20around%20the%20house.%20He%20%26quot%3Bjust%20couldn't%20get%20out%20of%20his%20own%20defensiveness%2C%26quot%3B%20Fern%20said.%20%26quot%3BSometimes%20we%20have%20a%20partner%20who%20isn't%20willing%20to%20do%20the%20work.%20And%20at%20some%20point%20it's%20like%2C%20OK%2C%20I%20can't%20do%20all%20of%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20relationship%20disintegrated%2C%20things%20were%20heating%20up%20with%20John%20from%20Feeld.%20%3Cstrong%3E%26quot%3B%3C%2Fstrong%3EI%20could%20feel%20it%20shifting%20where%20he%20was%20becoming%20my%20primary%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Fern%2C%20whose%20ex%20moved%20out%20in%20early%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Fern%20thinks%20abolishing%20relationship%20hierarchy%20is%20the%20ideal%2C%20and%20has%20seen%20some%20clients%20in%20triads%20who%20can%20genuinely%20have%20their%20heart%20in%20two%20places%20at%20once%2C%20she%20admitted%20it%20hasn't%20always%20worked%20for%20her.%20%26quot%3BI%20probably%20function%20more%20in%20a%20way%20where%20my%20heart%20has%20the%20primary%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20that%20looks%20like%20in%20practice%20is%20this%3A%20Right%20now%2C%20the%20queen%20of%20polysecurity%20is%20as%20happy%20as%20she's%20ever%20been%20in%20a%20pretty%20conventional%2C%20heterosexual%2C%20monogamous%20relationship.%20Though%20she%20hasn't%20quite%20solved%20the%20perennial%20poly%20problem%20of%20juggling%20multiple%20straight%2C%20cis%20male%20egos%20%E2%80%94%20%26quot%3Bif%20I%20dated%20a%20woman%2C%20it%20would%20be%20easier%26quot%3B%20than%20dating%20%26quot%3Banother%20masculine%20man%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20noted%20%E2%80%94%20Fern%20isn't%20trying%20to%20add%20anyone%20else%20into%20the%20mix%20right%20now.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20no%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20Fern%20said.%20%26quot%3BOr%20if%20there%20is%20a%20desire%2C%20wiser%20parts%20of%20me%20are%20like%2C%20that's%20just%20a%20desire.%26quot%3B%20Cooley%20is%20on%20the%20same%20page%2C%20albeit%20for%20different%20reasons.%20%26quot%3BI've%20found%20my%20bandwidth%20is%20very%2C%20very%20limited%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BPartly%20that's%20circumstantial%2C%20but%20partly%20it's%20just%20my%20nervous%20system.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWalking%20around%20Asheville%20with%20Fern%2C%20it's%20clear%20that%20she's%20as%20susceptible%20as%20anyone%20to%20the%20spine-tingling%20power%20of%20new%20relationship%20energy.%20You%20can%20practically%20see%20heart%20emojis%20forming%20in%20her%20eyes%20when%20she%20talks%20about%20John.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20still%20in%20love%2C%20and%20yeah%2C%20it's%20super%20sweet%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20She%20wears%20a%20gold%20%26quot%3Bopen%20lock%26quot%3B%20necklace%20that%20he%20gave%20her%20to%20symbolize%20their%20relationship.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20feeling%20is%20mutual.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20want%20to%20put%20her%20on%20a%20pedestal%20or%20anything%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20she's%20like%20%26quot%3Ba%20higher%20being%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20John%2C%20who%20has%20no%20idea%20what%20his%20attachment%20style%20is.%20%26quot%3BUh%2C%20you'd%20have%20to%20ask%20her.%20She%20usually%20keeps%20track%20of%20all%20of%20my%20INFP%2C%20whatever%2C%20those%20kind%20of%20things%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20(INFP%20is%20a%20subtype%20on%20the%20Myers-Briggs%20personality%20test).%20%26quot%3BI%20always%20think%20it's%20just%20normal.%20I%20just%20need%20the%20normal%20things.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOccasionally%2C%20elements%20of%20Fern's%20disorganized%20childhood-attachment%20style%20still%20bubble%20up%20in%20new%20relationships.%20Early%20on%2C%20she%20and%20John%20were%20seeing%20each%20other%20just%20once%20or%20twice%20a%20week%2C%20which%20made%20her%20%26quot%3Bget%20really%20wobbly%26quot%3B%20and%20lean%20into%20avoidance.%20So%20in%20December%2C%20they%20switched%20to%20three%20times%20a%20week%2C%20%26quot%3Band%20that%20has%20literally%20solved%20it.%26quot%3B%20It%20was%20that%20simple.%20And%2C%20yes%2C%20though%20it's%20a%20polyamory%20clich%C3%A9%2C%20a%20shared%20Google%20calendar%20helped%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%20for%20the%20most%20part%2C%20while%20John%20had%20never%20been%20to%20therapy%20or%20read%20any%20books%20about%20it%2C%20he%20seemed%20to%20know%20instinctively%20how%20to%20meet%20Fern's%20needs.%20(He%20tried%20to%20listen%20to%20%26quot%3BPolysecure%26quot%3B%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Eand%20%26quot%3BPolywise%26quot%3B%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Eon%20audiobook%20after%20they%20started%20dating%2C%20but%20it%20was%20%26quot%3Bsomewhat%20over%20my%20head%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.)%20%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20simplicity%20and%20straightforwardness%26quot%3B%20where%20he%20can%20%26quot%3Bsay%20what%20he%20needs%20and%20he%20doesn't%20make%20it%20anything%20more%2C%26quot%3B%20Fern%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhich%20gets%20to%20the%20problem%20with%20self-help%20books%20in%20general%3A%20Ultimately%2C%20there's%20only%20so%20much%20you%20can%20teach.%20Sometimes%2C%20all%20a%20person%20needs%20is%20a%20reformed%20bull%20who%20shows%20up%20in%20their%20life%20when%20they%20least%20expect%20it%2C%20is%20great%20at%20listening%2C%20and%20fucks%20them%20just%20how%20they%20want%20to%20be%20fucked.%20Fern%20dragged%20John%20to%20some%20mostly%20%26quot%3Bpreventative%26quot%3B%20couples%20therapy%20sessions%2C%20she%20said%2C%20but%20they%20only%20lasted%20a%20few%20months%20before%20their%20counselor%20sent%20them%20packing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BShe's%20like%2C%20you%20all%20are%20good%2C%26quot%3B%20Fern%20said%2C%20blushing.%20%26quot%3BJust%20reach%20out%20when%20you%20have%20a%20problem.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjessica-fern-polysecure-book-consensual-nonmonogamy-polyamory-2024-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1725530403000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66d8645814a5cd1fcc8d00f3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjessica-fern-polysecure-book-consensual-nonmonogamy-polyamory-2024-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Jessica%20Fern's%202020%20sleeper%20hit%20%26quot%3BPolysecure%26quot%3B%20has%20become%20the%20new%20polyamory%20bible%20%E2%80%94%20and%20a%20status%20symbol%20for%20the%20sexually%20enlightened.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22asilman%40insider.com%20(Anna%20Silman)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjessica-fern-polysecure-book-consensual-nonmonogamy-polyamory-2024-9%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Inside%20America's%20wildest%20%26amp%3Bmdash%3B%20and%20most%20lucrative%20%26amp%3Bmdash%3B%20lawsuits%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223600%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20skull%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20objects%20that%20have%20been%20subject%20to%20mass%20torts.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66d72646289b805d1db38f61%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221800%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EChristian%20Northeast%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMike%20Papantonio%20is%20an%20evangelist%20for%20the%20gospel%20of%20mass%20torts.%20The%2070-year-old%20shares%20the%20good%20news%20with%20his%20flock%20twice%20a%20year%20at%20the%20Wynn%20Las%20Vegas%20during%20the%20raucous%20Mass%20Torts%20Made%20Perfect%20conference.%20%26quot%3BYou're%20going%20to%20do%20well%20financially%20doing%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20tells%20his%20fellow%20lawyers%2C%20%26quot%3Bbut%20you're%20also%20going%20to%20do%20something%20that%20has%20some%20impact.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPap%2C%20as%20his%20disciples%20call%20him%2C%20isn't%20wrong.%20Mass%20torts%20have%20generated%20well%20over%20%2450%20billion%20for%20injury%20victims%20and%20their%20lawyers%20since%20the%201980s.%20Opioid%20prescriptions%20have%20fallen%2C%20asbestos%20has%20been%20phased%20out%2C%20and%20dangerous%20drugs%20like%20fen-phen%20have%20been%20pulled%20largely%20because%20of%20mass-tort%20lawsuits.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcancer-patient-18m-from-johnson-and-johnson-baby-powder-bankruptcy-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJohnson%20%26amp%3B%20Johnson%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20making%20its%20baby%20powder%20with%20cornstarch%20instead%20of%20talc%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ebecause%20of%20mass-tort%20lawsuits%20linking%20talc%20to%20cancer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20for%20all%20the%20impact%2C%20and%20the%20money%2C%20mass%20torts%20are%20little%20known%20to%20outsiders.%20The%20%26quot%3Bmass%26quot%3B%20part%20is%20obvious%2C%20and%20%26quot%3Btorts%26quot%3B%20is%20a%20lawyerly%20word%20that%20boils%20down%20to%20any%20kind%20of%20harm%20or%20injury.%20They%20exist%20at%20the%20boundary%20between%20public%20harm%20and%20private%20resolutions%3A%20Depending%20on%20how%20you%20count%2C%20between%20400%2C000%20and%206%20million%20Americans%20were%20part%20of%20a%20mass-tort%20case%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou've%20certainly%20seen%20the%20ads%3A%20Have%20you%20been%20hurt%20by%20Roundup%2C%20Zantac%2C%20pelvic%20mesh%2C%20or%20contaminated%20water%20at%20Camp%20Lejeune%3F%20Did%20your%20kid%20develop%20ADHD%2C%20depression%2C%20or%20necrotizing%20enterocolitis%3F%20You%20may%20be%20entitled%20to%20compensation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMass%20Torts%20Made%20Perfect%20is%20part%20of%20the%20reason%20the%20field%20has%20gotten%20so%20big.%20For%20about%20a%20quarter%20of%20a%20century%2C%20thousands%20of%20lawyers%20who%20handle%20slip-and-falls%20and%20medical-malpractice%20cases%20have%20attended%20the%20conference.%20When%20they%20get%20home%2C%20they%20spin%20up%20side%20hustles%20referring%20Roundup%2C%20Zantac%2C%20and%20hernia-mesh%20cases%20to%20firms%20like%20Pap's%20that%20go%20toe%20to%20toe%20with%20the%20pharma%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Egiants%20of%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20over%20the%20past%20several%20years%2C%20some%20lawyers%20%E2%80%94%20and%20investors%20bankrolling%20them%20%E2%80%94%20have%20found%20that%20mass%20torts%20are%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Egetting%20harder%20to%20monetize.%20Advertising%20is%20thought%20to%20eat%20up%20somewhere%20between%2012%25%20and%2050%25%20of%20the%20budgets%20of%20mass-tort%20firms.%20At%20a%20recent%20conference%2C%20Paul%20Cody%2C%20whose%20firm%20Counsel%20Financial%20says%20it%20has%20lent%20more%20than%20%241.5%20billion%20to%20law%20firms%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eestimated%20that%20at%20least%20two%20dozen%20plaintiffs'%20firms%20each%20had%20a%20debt%20load%20of%20at%20least%20%24100%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESettlements%20are%20often%20taking%20longer%20than%20lawyers%20and%20investors%20budgeted%20for%2C%20leaving%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20plaintiffs%20in%20limbo.%20Johnson%20%26amp%3B%20Johnson%20is%20trying%20for%20the%20third%20time%20to%20spin%20off%20its%20talc-based-baby-powder%20liabilities%20into%20a%20shell%20company%20created%20to%20file%20for%20bankruptcy%20protection%2C%20eight%20years%20after%20the%20cases%20against%20it%20were%20lumped%20together.%20Bayer%20has%20said%20it%20won't%20settle%20any%20of%20the%2057%2C000%20Roundup%20cases%20it's%20facing%20until%20they%20go%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20wily%20world%20of%20mass%20torts%2C%20the%20maxim%20that%20America%20is%20a%20nation%20of%20laws%20is%20strained%20past%20its%20breaking%20point.%20But%20the%20outcomes%2C%20people%20on%20both%20sides%20say%2C%20still%20resemble%20rough%20justice.%20Consumers%20who%20used%20products%20without%20knowing%20the%20risks%20get%20paid%2C%20and%20businesses%20that%20hid%20the%20dangers%20of%20those%20products%20can%20settle%20cases%20in%20bulk%20instead%20of%20facing%20decades%20of%20trials%20and%20occasional%20billion-dollar%20verdicts%20that%20make%20investors%20nervous.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20the%20rules%20don't%20fit%20what%20we%20do%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Chris%20Seeger%2C%20a%20prominent%20mass-tort%20plaintiffs'%20attorney.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20improvising%20and%20calling%20audibles%20all%20the%20time.%20There%20just%20aren't%20rules%20on%20point%20for%20litigation%20that%20involves%20100%2C000%20claims.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20most%20of%20US%20history%2C%20injured%20people%20were%20rarely%20able%20to%20sue%2C%20and%20when%20they%20did%2C%20judges%20put%20a%20low%20price%20on%20their%20pain.%20In%201892%2C%20confronted%20with%20a%20dockworker%20who%20lost%20a%20leg%2C%20a%20judge%20wrote%2C%20%26quot%3BHis%20disability%20is%20for%20life%2C%20but%20for%20life%20only%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20awarded%20%24500%20for%20his%20suffering%2C%20or%20about%20%2417%2C000%20in%20today's%20dollars.%20Presumably%2C%20the%20judge%20implied%2C%20the%20one-legged%20man%20could%20collect%20the%20rest%20of%20his%20reward%20in%20the%20afterlife.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20the%201960s%2C%20that%20was%20changing.%20Cars%20became%20ubiquitous%2C%20and%20car-crash%20lawsuits%20became%20a%20cottage%20industry.%20More%20Americans%20turned%20to%20the%20courts%2C%20jury%20verdicts%20got%20bigger%2C%20and%20the%20legal%20system%20needed%20new%20ways%20to%20handle%20complex%2C%20high-stakes%20lawsuits%20that%20didn't%20involve%20every%20single%20injured%2C%20ripped-off%2C%20or%20discriminated-against%20person%20having%20their%20day%20in%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EClass%20actions%2C%20which%20allowed%20one%20person%20to%20represent%20millions%20of%20others%2C%20were%20one%20solution.%20Lawyers%20could%20win%20enormous%20payouts%20%E2%80%94%20for%20themselves%2C%20yes%2C%20but%20also%20ripped-off%20consumers%2C%20endangered%20workers%2C%20and%20scammed%20investors%20%E2%80%94%20based%20on%20a%20single%20representative%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMass%20torts%2C%20which%20are%20less%20rules-based%20and%20more%20opaque%2C%20were%20another%20approach.%20Early%20cases%20were%20often%20local%2C%20like%20when%20a%20few%20hundred%20people%20sued%20a%20toxin-spewing%20chemical%20plant%20or%20when%20the%20families%20of%20plane-crash%20victims%20sued%20an%20airline.%20In%20the%201970s%2C%20mass%20torts%20went%20national.%20Hundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20women%20sued%20over%20defective%20IUDs%2C%20and%20revelations%20that%20asbestos%20caused%20cancer%20led%20to%20an%20unprecedented%20wave%20of%20claims%20that%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20eventually%20ruled%20were%20too%20different%20from%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eone%20another%20to%20be%20settled%20as%20a%20class%20action.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20the%20key%20distinguisher%20for%20mass%20torts%3A%20Every%20case%20gets%20filed%20individually.%20More%20than%20700%2C000%20asbestos%20cases%20have%20been%20filed%2C%20and%20its%20victims%20have%20received%20at%20least%20%2417%20billion.%20Some%20of%20their%20lawyers%2C%20who%20get%20paid%20a%20portion%20of%20each%20recovery%2C%20became%20millionaires%20many%20times%20over.%20A%20law%20professor%20said%20in%202002%20that%20just%20two%20firms%20%E2%80%94%20Baron%20%26amp%3B%20Budd%20in%20Texas%20and%20Ness%20Motley%20(later%20Motley%20Rice)%20in%20South%20Carolina%20%E2%80%94%20represented%20about%20half%20of%20asbestos%20victims.%20If%20those%20two%20firms%20worked%20up%20the%20cases%20themselves%20and%20didn't%20have%20to%20split%20fees%20with%20anyone%20else%2C%20they%20could%20have%20made%20over%20%243%20billion%20in%20fees%20over%20the%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20mass-tort%20case%20usually%20starts%20small%2C%20with%20a%20few%20people%20hurt%20by%20a%20drug%20or%20a%20medical%20device.%20Law%20firms%20typically%20accuse%20companies%20of%20failing%20to%20warn%20people%20about%20a%20product's%20risks.%20As%20more%20and%20more%20cases%20are%20filed%2C%20federal%20or%20state%20courts%20usually%20decide%20to%20centralize%20and%20simplify%20them.%20Judges%20may%20charge%20a%20%26quot%3Bsteering%20committee%26quot%3B%20of%20victims'%20lawyers%20with%20doling%20out%20work%20and%20negotiating%20with%20the%20defendant%20about%20document%20production%2C%20trials%2C%20and%20settlement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20a%20marketing%20machine%20roars%20to%20life.%20The%20data%20provider%20X%20Ante%20estimated%20that%20in%202023%2C%20mass-tort%20lawyers%20spent%20%3Cu%3E%24152%20million%3C%2Fu%3E%20on%20TV%20ads%20and%20millions%20more%20on%20social%20media.%20Call-center%20operators%20screen%20potential%20clients%20to%20vet%20viable%20cases%2C%20and%20nurses%20and%20paralegals%20review%20medical%20records%20and%20prepare%20the%20documents%20needed%20to%20file%20suit.%20(Attorneys%20on%20the%20defense%20side%20of%20a%20mass%20tort%20often%20accuse%20injury%20lawyers%20and%20their%20marketing%20partners%20of%20cutting%20corners%20and%20of%20bringing%20fraudulent%20or%20legally%20suspect%20claims.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20decades%20that%20followed%20mass%20torts'%20onset%20on%20the%20national%20stage%20showed%20the%20big%20risks%20and%20big%20rewards%20of%20mass%20torts.%20When%20more%20than%20200%2C000%20women%20brought%20claims%20over%20silicone-gel%20breast%20implants%20in%20the%201990s%2C%20a%20company%20that%20made%20them%20filed%20for%20bankruptcy.%20That%20led%20to%20a%20law%20firm%20representing%20800%20of%20those%20women%20to%20file%20for%20bankruptcy%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI've%20seen%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20come%20and%20go%20in%20mass%20torts%2C%26quot%3B%20Seeger%20says.%20%26quot%3BI%20could%20give%20you%20a%20list%20of%20firms%20that%20have%20been%20wiped%20out%20by%20them.%26quot%3B%20But%20plenty%20of%20lawyers%20have%20repeated%20the%20successes%20of%20the%20asbestos%20barons.%20In%20the%20early%202000s%2C%20Wyeth%2C%20now%20part%20of%20Pfizer%2C%20initially%20budgeted%20%242.6%20billion%20to%20settle%20cases%20over%20its%20diet%20drug%20fen-phen.%20Facing%20a%20volume%20of%20cases%20that%20was%20far%20larger%20than%20projected%20%E2%80%94%20many%20of%20which%20were%20later%20found%20to%20be%20fraudulent%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.law.com%2Famericanlawyer%2FalmID%2F1109128224002%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eit%20ended%20up%20paying%20more%20than%20%2420%20billion%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EWhich%20specific%20lawyers%20and%20injured%20citizens%20get%20paid%2C%20and%20precisely%20how%20much%2C%20is%20something%20of%20a%20mystery.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20class%20action%2C%20a%20settlement%20is%20public%2C%20and%20the%20judge%20has%20to%20approve%20the%20lawyers'%20fees.%20Any%20class%20member%20can%20take%20issue%20with%20the%20proposed%20deal%20and%20fees%2C%20and%20judges%20often%20end%20up%20cutting%20the%20fees.%20In%20mass%20torts%2C%20settlements%20are%20usually%20secret%20and%20could%20vary%20depending%20on%20which%20firm%20someone%20signs%20up%20with.%20In%20the%20end%2C%20clients%20are%20usually%20offered%20settlements%20spit%20out%20by%20a%20formula%20based%20on%20their%20ages%2C%20whether%20they%20smoked%20cigarettes%2C%20how%20long%20they%20used%20a%20drug%20or%20were%20exposed%20to%20a%20potential%20toxin%2C%20and%20similar%20factors.%20Lawyers%20can%20collect%20a%20contingency%20fee%2C%20often%20about%2040%25%2C%20from%20all%20their%20clients%2C%20with%20no%20judicial%20sign-off%20required%20and%20few%20ways%20for%20a%20client%20to%20object.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPhil%20Federico%2C%20a%20Baltimore%20medical-malpractice%20lawyer%2C%20recalled%20deciding%20to%20go%20whole%20hog%20into%20mass%20torts%20after%20a%20friend%20introduced%20him%20to%20an%20attorney%20in%20a%20three-piece%20suit%20named%20Paul%20Hanly%20who'd%20made%20it%20big%20after%20switching%20from%20repping%20asbestos%20companies%20to%20repping%20their%20victims.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGoing%20around%20with%20him%20in%20NYC%2C%20in%20his%20Bentley%2C%20from%20the%20restaurant%20to%20the%20bar%2C%26quot%3B%20Federico%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20said%2C%20'What%20do%20you%20do%20for%20a%20living%3F'%20He%20said%2C%20'I'm%20a%20mass-tort%20lawyer.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFederico%20said%20he%20was%20an%20early%20mover%20on%20the%20famous%20Camp%20Lejeune%20cases%2C%20in%20which%20Marines%20and%20their%20families%20sued%20the%20US%20government%20over%20medical%20conditions%20caused%20by%20contaminated%20water%20at%20a%20North%20Carolina%20base.%20While%20other%20lawyers%20pumped%20millions%20into%20ads%2C%20Federico%20said%2C%20he%20took%20a%20cheaper%20route%20of%20networking%20with%20Marines%2C%20epidemiologists%2C%20and%20groups%20like%20the%20Veterans%20of%20Foreign%20Wars.%20Of%20the%20more%20than%20200%2C000%20people%20who've%20brought%20Camp%20Lejeune%20claims%2C%20he%20was%20able%20to%20sign%20up%202%2C000%20with%20the%20strongest%20cases%20for%20about%20%24400%20to%20%24500%20each.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFederico's%20high-touch%20approach%20is%20relatively%20rare.%20Many%20mass-tort%20lawyers%20don't%20develop%20their%20own%20cases%20at%20all%3B%20they%20buy%20leads%20or%20sign%20co-counsel%20agreements%20with%20other%20firms%20and%20agree%20to%20split%20fees.%20Referrals%20are%20the%20coin%20of%20the%20realm%20in%20mass%20torts%2C%20and%20they%20are%20facilitated%20by%20connections%20that%20lawyers%20make%20at%20conferences%20like%20Pap's%20Mass%20Torts%20Made%20Perfect%2C%20the%20mack%20daddy%20of%20mass-tort%20gatherings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20like%20the%20mass-tort%20bar's%20Burning%20Man%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Curt%20Miner%2C%20an%20occasional%20attendee.%20%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20cool%20stuff%20goes%20on%20there%2C%20but%20also%20a%20lot%20of%20craziness.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20attendee%20from%20this%20April's%20conference%20said%20that%20after%20days%20filled%20with%20panels%20about%20science%2C%20deposition%20tactics%2C%20and%20civil%20procedure%2C%20a%20%26quot%3Bwork%20hard%2C%20play%20hard%26quot%3B%20attitude%20takes%20hold%20at%20night.%20%26quot%3BI've%20seen%20lawyers%20doing%20coke%20off%20strippers'%20boobs%2C%26quot%3B%20another%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20years%2C%20the%20standup%20comic%20turned%20trial%20lawyer%20Don%20Worley%20unofficially%20kicked%20off%20the%20conference%20with%20his%20popular%20%26quot%3Blittle-people%20parties%2C%26quot%3B%20featuring%20scantily%20clad%20models%20and%20boxing%20matches%20between%20entertainers%20with%20dwarfism.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20ridiculous%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20mass-tort%20lawyer%20who%20caught%20wind%20of%20the%20event%20said%2C%20and%20%26quot%3Bembarrassing%20to%20the%20plaintiffs'%20bar.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWorley%20isn't%20allowed%20to%20come%20to%20Pap's%20conference%20anymore.%20%26quot%3BThe%20day%20of%20the%20cowboy%20lawyer%20is%20long%20gone%2C%26quot%3B%20Pap%20said.%20Worley%20said%20the%20only%20reason%20he%20got%20the%20boot%20was%20that%20he%20struck%20up%20referral%20relationships%20with%20lawyers%20%E2%80%94%20about%20400%2C%20he%20said%20%E2%80%94%20and%20Pap%20would%20rather%20keep%20that%20referral%20business%20for%20himself.%20Pap%20called%20that%20%26quot%3Bhorseshit.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Marines%20sailors%20Camp%20Lejeune%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5fc7d18f50e71a0011558709%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22877%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMore%20than%20200%2C000%20Marines%20and%20their%20families%20have%20sued%20the%20US%20government%20over%20medical%20conditions%20caused%20by%20contaminated%20water%20at%20Camp%20Lejeune.%3Cp%3EUS%20Marine%20Corps%2FCpl.%20Daniel%20A.%20Wulz%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20referrals%20alone%20don't%20get%20anybody%20paid.%20Nearly%20all%20mass-tort%20cases%20settle%2C%20usually%20for%20a%20fraction%20of%20whichever%20verdicts%20were%20racked%20up%20in%20the%20%26quot%3Bbellwether%20trials%26quot%3B%20that%20lawyers%20run%20to%20test%20the%20waters%2C%20and%20the%20money%20flows%20in%20the%20years%20that%20follow.%20In%20federal%20mass-tort%20proceedings%2C%20fewer%20than%203%25%20of%20cases%20end%20up%20getting%20tried.%20One%20law%20professor%20wrote%20that%20defense%20lawyers%20joke%20that%20mass%20torts%20are%20like%20%26quot%3Bthe%20Outback%20Steakhouse%20of%20litigation%3A%20'No%20Rules%2C%20Just%20Right.'%26quot%3B%20They%20feel%20they%20would%20win%20if%20judges%20enforced%20the%20rules%20instead%20of%20trying%20to%20jawbone%20them%20into%20a%20settlement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20victims%20of%20corporate%20wrongdoing%20also%20want%20their%20day%20in%20court.%20But%20lawyers%20say%20few%20of%20them%20would%20feel%20that%20way%20if%20they%20realized%20they%20may%20have%20to%20spend%20six%20weeks%20in%20a%20courtroom%20and%20risk%20walking%20away%20with%20nothing%20to%20pay%20the%20bills.%20Mark%20Lanier%2C%20a%20Texas%20trial%20lawyer%2C%20has%20a%20saying%3A%20%26quot%3BSettlements%20feed%20families%2C%20trials%20feed%20egos.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20inconsistency%20of%20mass%20torts%20doesn't%20annoy%20only%20defendants.%20Sometimes%20injury%20lawyers%20go%20to%20war%20against%20each%20other.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20past%20few%20months%2C%20Pap%20has%20been%20blasting%20his%20Mass%20Torts%20Made%20Perfect%20mailing%20list%20with%20attacks%20on%20law%20firms%20that%20struck%20a%20deal%20with%20Johnson%20%26amp%3B%20Johnson%20to%20use%20bankruptcy%20to%20settle%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20its%20talc-based-powder%20lawsuits.%20Women%20with%20ovarian%20cancer%20would%20get%20%2450%2C000%20to%20%24200%2C000%2C%20an%20amount%20he%20says%20is%20inadequate%20to%20pay%20for%20their%20medical%20care%2C%20much%20less%20to%20compensate%20them%20for%20their%20pain.%20Women%20with%20other%20gynecological%20cancers%20lacking%20as%20strong%20of%20an%20association%20with%20talc%20would%20get%20only%20%241%2C500.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20numbers%20they%20have%20are%20just%20fantasy%20numbers%2C%26quot%3B%20Pap%20says.%20He%20said%20his%20team%20hired%20a%20private%20investigator%20to%20call%20J%26amp%3BJ%20posing%20as%20claimants.%20%26quot%3BWe%20had%20them%20saying%3A%20'I%20was%20around%20J%26amp%3BJ%20baby%20powder%20for%20three%20weeks%2C%20and%20now%20I%20have%20esophageal%20cancer.%20Do%20I%20have%20a%20case%3F'%20And%20they'd%20say%2C%20'Yeah%2C%20yeah%2C%20go%20online%20and%20get%20the%20papers%20for%20that.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20talc%20cases%2C%20Pap's%20firm%20is%20on%20the%20steering%20committee%2C%20a%20coalition%20of%20lawyers%20appointed%20by%20the%20judge%20to%20allocate%20work%20for%20the%20benefit%20of%20all%20the%20plaintiffs%20and%20to%20negotiate%20with%20defendants.%20Their%20work%20is%20paid%20for%20by%20a%20tax%20on%20everyone's%20settlement%2C%20typically%205%20to%207%20percentage%20points%20of%20the%20contingency%20fee%20the%20client%20has%20already%20agreed%20to%20with%20the%20lawyer%20they%20retained.%20These%20taxes%2C%20known%20as%20%26quot%3Bcommon%20benefit%26quot%3B%20fees%2C%20are%20contentious%3B%20one%20judge%20said%20in%202021%20that%20they%20were%20%26quot%3Btotally%20out%20of%20control.%26quot%3B%20But%20Pap%20calls%20it%20a%20way%20to%20stop%20free%20riders.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGenerally%2C%20there%20are%20two%20kinds%20of%20mass-tort%20lawyers%3A%20those%20who%20specialize%20in%20finding%20clients%2C%20and%20those%20who%20specialize%20in%20litigating%20cases%20and%20hammering%20out%20settlements.%20The%20relationship%20is%20mutually%20beneficial%3A%20The%20litigators%20and%20negotiators%20wouldn't%20have%20leverage%20without%20thousands%20of%20cases%2C%20and%20the%20case-acquisition%20specialists%20wouldn't%20know%20what%20they%20were%20doing%20if%20they%20had%20to%20go%20it%20alone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20top%20tier%20can%20be%20clubby.%20Newcomers%20try%20to%20hitch%20their%20wagons%20to%20leaders%20%E2%80%94%20or%2C%20more%20realistically%2C%20to%20someone%20who%20knows%20a%20leader.%20Seeger%20may%20be%20the%20most%20powerful%20mass-tort%20lawyer%20in%20America.%20Elizabeth%20Chamblee%20Burch%2C%20a%20law%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Georgia%2C%20studied%2073%20mass%20torts%20and%20found%20that%20Seeger%20had%20been%20appointed%20to%20leadership%20roles%20in%2021%20of%20them.%20His%20clients%20have%20included%20NFL%20players%20with%20brain%20damage%2C%20veterans%20who%20alleged%20their%20hearing%20was%20damaged%20by%20defective%20earplugs%2C%20and%20victims%20of%20the%20opioid%20crisis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20concentration%20of%20authority%20in%20a%20relatively%20small%20group%20of%20lawyers%20has%20its%20critics%2C%20including%20Burch%2C%20who%20argued%20that%20relying%20on%20%26quot%3Brepeat%20players%26quot%3B%20had%20resulted%20in%20mass-tort%20settlements%20that%20put%20lawyers'%20interests%20above%20their%20clients'%20interests.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Seeger%20and%20other%20lawyers%20at%20the%20top%20of%20the%20heap%20say%20that%20putting%20inexperienced%20lawyers%20in%20charge%20of%20a%20mass%20tort%20is%20a%20great%20way%20to%20get%20a%20bad%20deal.%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20really%20more%20art%20than%20science%2C%20and%20not%20everyone%20is%20good%20at%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEllen%20Relkin%2C%20a%20mass-torts%20lawyer%20who%20has%20sued%20several%20artificial-hip%20makers%2C%20put%20it%20another%20way.%20%26quot%3BThere%20are%20doctors%20who%20fix%20broken%20bones%20and%20give%20steroid%20shots%2C%20and%20they%20learned%20in%20residency%20how%20to%20do%20hips%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BAre%20you%20going%20to%20go%20to%20him%20or%20her%2C%20or%20are%20you%20going%20to%20go%20to%20the%20person%20who%20does%20five%20hips%20a%20day%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELeading%20a%20mass%20tort%20isn't%20just%20a%20matter%20of%20skill%3B%20it%20is%20expensive%20to%20work%20up%20cases%2C%20analyze%20medical%20records%2C%20obtain%20discovery%20from%20defendants%2C%20and%20sort%20through%20millions%20of%20pages%20of%20emails%2C%20memos%2C%20and%20scientific%20analysis.%20In%20%3Cu%3Ea%202020%20interview%3C%2Fu%3E%2C%20Seeger%20said%20he%20and%20other%20lead%20lawyers%20suing%20Merck%20over%20undisclosed%20risks%20of%20the%20arthritis%20drug%20Vioxx%20spent%20%2441%20million%20before%20their%20clients%20saw%20a%20dime.%20Few%20plaintiffs'%20lawyers%20have%20that%20kind%20of%20money.%20There's%20also%20something%20to%20be%20said%20for%20experience%3A%20Deep-pocketed%20companies%20hire%20the%20same%20lawyers%20over%20and%20over%2C%20too%2C%20and%20they%20can%20run%20circles%20around%20inexperienced%20plaintiffs'%20lawyers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20it's%20not%20just%20wealthy%20asbestos%20lawyers%20who%20call%20the%20shots%20anymore.%20The%20composition%20of%20the%20power%20players%20of%20mass-tort%20lawyering%20is%20changing%2C%20said%20Lucian%20Pera%2C%20a%20legal-ethics%20advisor%20who%20has%20clients%20in%20mass%20torts.%20%26quot%3BThere%20are%20way%20more%20of%20them%2C%20and%20there%20are%20way%20more%20categories%20of%20them%26quot%3B%20than%20there%20were%2010%20or%2015%20years%20ago%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20new%20entrant%20to%20the%20top%20tier%20is%20Keller%20Postman.%20It%20popularized%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-plaintiffs-law-firms-bring-mass-arbitration-cases-class-actions-2021-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Emass%20arbitration%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20turned%20the%20arbitration%20clauses%20that%20big%20businesses%20bury%20in%20their%20terms%20of%20service%20to%20avoid%20lawsuits%20into%20a%20weapon%20to%20use%20against%20them.%20But%20the%20firm%20also%20litigates%20more-traditional%20mass%20torts%3A%20It%20has%20signed%20up%20people%20by%20the%20thousands%20to%20sue%20over%20products%20like%20Enfamil%20and%20Similac%2C%20Zantac%2C%20and%203M's%20Combat%20Arms%20earplugs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20lawyers%20who%20help%20Keller%20Postman%20find%20clients%20is%20Jeremy%20Troxel%2C%20who%20spends%20at%20least%20six%20figures%20a%20year%20on%20Facebook%20ads%20to%20drum%20up%20clients%20for%20Keller%20and%20others.%20The%20value%20of%20his%20work%20is%20clear%20in%20fee%20agreements%20seen%20by%20Business%20Insider%3A%20A%20retainer%20for%20a%20victim%20of%20the%20toxic%20water%20at%20Camp%20Lejeune%20specifies%20the%2040%25%20fee%20will%20be%20split%2050-50%20between%20Troxel%20and%20Keller.%20A%20retainer%20for%20Keller%20to%20pursue%20Intuit%20over%20TurboTax%20fees%20says%20Troxel%20gets%2010%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20appears%20to%20be%20going%20well%20for%20Troxel.%20He%20was%20recently%20spotted%20buying%20a%20%2415%20million%20home%20once%20owned%20by%20Rihanna%20in%20Beverly%20Hills%2C%20California.%20He%20didn't%20reply%20to%20emails.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3ETantalized%20by%20mass-tort%20windfalls%2C%20investors%20have%20increasingly%20funneled%20cash%20to%20lawyers.%20The%20consulting%20firm%20Morning%20Investments%20estimated%20last%20year%20that%20about%20a%20sixth%20of%20the%20roughly%206%20million%20mass-tort%20cases%20in%20its%20dataset%20had%20outside%20funding.%20Those%20funded%20cases%20were%20worth%20about%20%2417%20billion%2C%20and%20in%20recent%20years%20the%20internal%20rate%20of%20return%20on%20mass-tort%20investments%20has%20typically%20been%20between%2020%25%20and%2030%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELaw%20firms%20have%20trouble%20getting%20banks%20to%20lend%20to%20them%20for%20all%20but%20the%20safest%20cases%2C%20so%20much%20of%20the%20capital%20flows%20from%20nonbanks%20seeking%20higher%20returns.%20Funds%20managed%20by%20the%20likes%20of%20Fortress%20Investment%20Group%20and%20Gramercy%20Funds%20have%20poured%20hundreds%20of%20millions%20of%20dollars%20into%20law%20firms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20these%20investments%2C%20however%2C%20have%20been%20costly%20blunders%20that%20toed%20the%20line%20of%20criminality.%20Lenders%20and%20surgeons%20who%20teamed%20up%20to%20remove%20pelvic%20meshes%20from%20women%20in%20hopes%20of%20collecting%20money%20from%20whatever%20the%20women%20were%20able%20to%20get%20in%20a%20settlement%20with%20mesh%20manufacturers%20faced%20prosecutions%20and%20civil%20lawsuits.%20An%20attorney%20who%20used%20borrowed%20money%20to%20bring%20a%20case%20on%20behalf%20of%20thousands%20of%20Vietnamese%20fishermen%20whose%20livelihoods%20had%20been%20destroyed%20by%20the%20Deepwater%20Horizon%20oil%20spill%20was%20criminally%20charged%20after%20it%20was%20revealed%20that%20their%20names%20had%20been%20copied%20from%20a%20phone%20book%3B%20he%20was%20acquitted%2C%20but%20two%20codefendants%20were%20convicted%20of%20fraud%20and%20identity%20theft.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAttorneys%20have%20gotten%20more%20cautious%20about%20what%20they%20will%20buy%2C%20and%20financiers%20have%20gotten%20pickier%20about%20what%20they%20will%20finance%2C%26quot%3B%20Morning%20Investments'%20president%2C%20Michael%20McDonald%2C%20said%20in%20an%20email.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWarren%20Postman%20of%20Keller%20Postman%20said%20his%20firm%20and%20others%20spent%20%26quot%3Btens%20of%20millions%20of%20dollars%26quot%3B%20on%20marketing%20in%20a%20case%20against%20makers%20of%20acetaminophen%2C%20arguing%20that%20manufacturers%20hid%20the%20risk%20that%20kids%20exposed%20to%20the%20drug%20before%20they%20were%20born%20could%20develop%20ADHD%20and%20autism.%20A%20federal%20judge%20dismissed%20the%20cases%20on%20evidentiary%20grounds%20%E2%80%94%20but%2C%20Postman%20noted%2C%20a%20successful%20appeal%20can%20turn%20everything%20around.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20meantime%2C%20interest%20is%20mounting%20for%20those%20firms%20borrowing%20money%20at%20rates%20that%20reflect%20the%20big%20risks%20involved%20in%20many%20cases%3B%20Morning%20Investments'%20data%20indicates%20lenders'%20internal%20rates%20of%20return%20in%20the%20past%20three%20years%20have%20ranged%20from%2021%25%20to%2025%25.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EIt's%20not%20clear%20how%20long%20these%20firms%20can%20keep%20rolling%20over%20their%20debt.%20Some%20lawyers%20are%20worried%20that%20the%20process%20makes%20it%20harder%20for%20clients%20to%20switch%20firms%20and%20puts%20undue%20pressure%20on%20lawyers%20to%20settle.%20But%20others%20are%20confident%20that%20indebted%20mass-tort%20lawyers%20can%20bounce%20back%20from%20a%20few%20bad%20bets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmerica%20has%20long%20been%20laissez-faire%20about%20regulating%20products%20that%20can%20harm%20people%2C%20and%20about%20the%20business%20of%20lawyering.%20Ethics%20codes%20and%20safety%20rules%20exist%2C%20but%20enforcing%20them%20is%20hard%2C%20especially%20when%20both%20sides%20can%20fund%20a%20robust%20defense.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20absent%20an%20overhaul%20of%20how%20Americans'%20medical%20bills%20are%20paid%2C%20what%20Pap%20preaches%20seems%20to%20be%20true.%20Mass%20torts%20are%20the%20best%20way%20the%20US%20has%20to%20right%20a%20wrong%3A%20Big%20businesses%20hurt%20people%2C%20and%20nobody%20makes%20them%20pay%20until%20lawyers%20step%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPap%20is%20skeptical%20of%20anyone%20who%20thinks%20they%20can%20become%20a%20mass-tort%20millionaire%20without%20paying%20their%20dues.%20And%20he's%20worried%20that%20the%20ills%20that%20have%20afflicted%20so%20much%20of%20modern%20American%20life%20are%20also%20coming%20for%20mass%20torts%3A%20complex%20financial%20machinations%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbig-cor