20a%20very%20significant%20gay%20community%2C%26quot%3B%20Allanach%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229cf8a6cf-f8fd-44b6-bd65-c0ea999b3b66%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EMoving%20to%20Canada%2C%20then%20Mexico%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAllanach%20was%20born%20and%20raised%20in%20Portland%2C%20Maine%2C%20where%20he%20started%20his%20career%20as%20a%20journalist.%20He%20worked%20on%20the%20police%20beat%20for%20a%20local%20newspaper%2C%20which%20led%20him%20to%20become%20a%20police%20officer%20after%20a%20short%20stint%20at%20the%20US%20Postal%20Inspection%20Service.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20over%20twenty%20years%2C%20Allanach%20worked%20in%20the%20police%20force%2C%20eventually%20becoming%20a%20police%20chief%20in%20the%20Portland%20area.%20He%20then%20earned%20master's%20degrees%20in%20public%20policy%20and%20education%20psychology%20and%20held%20positions%20as%20an%20education%20administrator%20and%20behavioral%20therapist.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20met%20his%20partner%20in%20his%20master's%20program%2C%20though%20Lorgeranon%2C%20who%20is%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fexpat-bangkok-thailand-better-life-low-cost-living-culture-home-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThailand%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20couldn't%20secure%20a%20residency%20in%20the%20US.%20Allanach%20suspected%20life%20in%20the%20US%20would%20be%20challenging%20as%20a%20same-sex%20couple%2C%20noting%20he%20became%20%26quot%3Bquite%20disenchanted%26quot%3B%20with%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUltimately%2C%20they%20decided%20to%20move%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fliving-in-city-where-tv-shows-are-filmed-vancouver-canadian-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EVancouver%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Allanach%20found%20work%20in%20the%20educational%20psychology%20department%20of%20various%20schools.%20Allanach%20and%20Lorgeranon%20agreed%20they%20lived%20a%20%26quot%3Bwonderful%20life%26quot%3B%20in%20Vancouver%20with%20many%20friends%20and%20cultural%20opportunities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoving-from-boston-nyc-brooklyn-worth-increased-costs-genz-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eliving%20expenses%3C%2Fa%3E%20started%20to%20rise%2C%20and%20he%20said%20his%20income%20was%20taxed%20at%20%2412%2C000%20one%20year.%20Even%20with%20a%20consistent%20salary%2C%20he%20couldn't%20see%20a%20comfortable%20future%20in%20Vancouver%2C%20knowing%20how%20rapidly%20the%20city%20was%20developing.%20At%20the%20time%2C%20he%20said%20healthcare%20was%20expensive%2C%20especially%20for%20dental%20care%2C%20and%20it%20was%20difficult%20to%20find%20open%20slots%20for%20medical%20appointments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20he%20found%20his%20area's%20politics%20shifting%20more%20toward%20the%20conservative%20viewpoint%2C%20and%20he%20felt%20increasingly%20uncomfortable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20retiring%20from%20the%20school%20board%2C%20Allanach%20put%20their%20820-square-foot%20Vancouver%20condo%20on%20the%20market%2C%20selling%20for%20over%20a%20million%20Canadian%20dollars%2C%20and%20decided%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvisited-all-50-states-best-worst-nyc-weather-kansas-washington-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etravel%20the%20world%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20a%20year%2C%20figuring%20expenses%20would%20be%20more%20or%20less%20equivalent%20to%20staying%20in%20Canada.%20They%20owned%20another%20apartment%20that%20sold%20for%20almost%20%24600%2C000%20CAD%20in%202014%2C%20though%20it's%20now%20valued%20at%20over%20%241.4%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20traveled%20to%20many%20European%20countries%2C%20staying%20in%20France%20for%20four%20months%2C%20and%20they%20spent%20time%20in%20Thailand%20with%20Allanach's%20partner's%20family.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAllanach%20wanted%20to%20move%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frelocate-chiang-mai-thailand-affordable-quality-of-life-best-city-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThailand%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20his%20retirement%2C%20but%20Thailand%20only%20grants%20permanent%20residency%20to%20100%20people%20per%20country%20each%20year.%20Allanach%20added%20the%20country%20often%20changes%20its%20rules%20surrounding%20visas%2C%20meaning%20living%20there%20long-term%20wouldn't%20be%20feasible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20visited%20M%C3%A9rida%2C%20the%20capital%20of%20Yucat%C3%A1n%20state%20in%20southeast%20Mexico%2C%20a%20few%20times%20starting%20in%202015%2C%20noting%20it%20was%20popular%20among%20expats%20but%20still%20had%20a%20vibrant%20local%20community.%20Allanach%20said%20they%20felt%20safer%20in%20M%C3%A9rida%20than%20in%20the%20US%20or%20Canada%2C%20and%20prices%20were%20lower.%20M%C3%A9rida%20has%20a%20population%20of%20about%201.2%20million%20as%20the%20financial%20capital%20of%20the%20Yucat%C3%A1n%20Peninsula.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202017%2C%20they%20bought%20a%201920%20colonial%20home%20in%20M%C3%A9rida%20from%20a%20Vancouver%20couple.%20They%20stayed%20there%20between%20trips%20back%20to%20Vancouver%2C%20and%20they%20moved%20to%20M%C3%A9rida%20fully%20in%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20of%20the%20things%20that's%20just%20a%20disaster%20for%20people%20moving%20to%20a%20foreign%20country%20is%20going%20there%20and%20expecting%20that%20you're%20going%20to%20make%20it%20like%20your%20home%20where%20you%20came%20from%2C%20and%20that's%20just%20not%20what%20happens%2C%26quot%3B%20Allanach%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22View%20from%20Ron%20Allanach's%20home%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66d8668a289b805d1db3f0e3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20street%20in%20M%C3%A9rida%2C%20Mexico.%3Cp%3ERon%20Allanach%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d22c938b-122c-4810-a317-f51331644007%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EGetting%20accustomed%20to%20M%C3%A9rida%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20Mexico%20opened%20to%20tourism%20after%20easing%20pandemic-related%20restrictions%2C%20Allanach%20met%20an%20architect%20from%20Los%20Angeles%20who%20moved%20to%20M%C3%A9rida%20and%20brought%20his%20practice%20with%20him.%20The%20architect%20built%20them%20a%202%2C800-square-foot%20home%2C%20which%20they%20have%20lived%20in%20for%20three%20years.%20The%20home%20cost%20them%20%24238%2C000%20and%20has%20three%20bedrooms%2C%20a%20full%20bath%2C%20a%20dining%20room%2C%20gardens%2C%20and%20a%20pool%20in%20the%20city%20center.%20Still%2C%20Allanach%20said%20home%20prices%20have%20risen%20fast%20as%20more%20expats%20come.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAllanach%20and%20Lorgeranon%20bought%20a%20car%20to%20explore%20the%20city%20and%20surrounding%20areas%20%E2%80%94%20which%20they%20park%20outside%20their%20home%20without%20any%20worries.%20They%20have%20tried%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerican-moving-living-mexico-what-expats-should-stop-doing-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eimmerse%20themselves%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20culture%20and%20history%20of%20the%20Mayan%20people%3B%20Allanach%20said%20they%20became%20very%20close%20with%20a%20local%20Indigenous%20family%20and%20paid%20tuition%20for%20their%20kid's%20school.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20meet%20people%20who%20say%2C%20I'm%20moving%20to%20M%C3%A9rida%2C%20but%20I%20know%20nothing%20about%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Allanach%20said%2C%20noting%20he's%20valued%20integrating%20into%20the%20community%20instead%20of%20only%20staying%20in%20expat%20areas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAllanach%20said%20he's%20been%20impressed%20by%20M%C3%A9rida's%20medical%20system%2C%20as%20he's%20often%20able%20to%20see%20a%20physician%20within%20an%20hour%20without%20being%20rushed.%20Many%20pharmacies%20near%20him%20are%20open%2024%2F7%2C%20and%20he%20often%20gets%2030%25%20to%2045%25%20off%20his%20prescriptions.%20He%20said%20doctors%20often%20make%20house%20calls%20in%20his%20part%20of%20the%20city%2C%20and%20seeing%20a%20doctor%20at%20a%20pharmacy%20costs%20just%20%242.50.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20M%C3%A9rida%20street%20with%20vintage%20cars%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66d866b51d8d2deb96b8835f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20M%C3%A9rida%20street%20with%20vintage%20cars%3Cp%3ERon%20Allanach%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20often%20get%20fresh%20produce%20at%20the%20Mercado%20Lucas%20de%20G%C3%A1lvez%2C%20though%20they%20often%20shop%20at%20Costco%20for%20larger%20purchases.%20He%20estimates%20their%20grocery%20bill%20is%20much%20higher%20in%20M%C3%A9rida%20than%20in%20Vancouver%2C%20given%20many%20items%20are%20imported.%20While%20there%20are%20many%20affordable%20restaurants%2C%20he%20said%20some%20restaurants%20catering%20more%20to%20tourists%20are%20%26quot%3Bvery%20expensive.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20saves%20hundreds%20of%20dollars%20yearly%20on%20auto%20insurance%2C%20which%20is%20%24500%20in%20Mexico%20for%20a%20new%20SUV%2C%20whereas%20he%20paid%20over%20%242%2C500%20in%20Vancouver.%20Whereas%20property%20taxes%20were%20about%20%241%2C700%20a%20year%20in%20Vancouver%2C%20they're%20just%20%24160%20a%20year%20in%20Mexico.%20They%20use%20solar%20energy%2C%20which%20was%20a%20one-time%20expense%20of%20%245%2C500%2C%20though%20Allanach%20said%20the%20electric%20bill%20during%20the%20summer%20could%20cost%20%24250%20to%20%24500%2C%20as%20the%20heat%20is%20sometimes%20difficult.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20costs%20include%20%2438%20yearly%20for%20trash%20pickup%2C%20%2430%20monthly%20for%205%2C000%20TV%20channels%2C%20%2435%20for%20pool%20service%2C%20and%20%2460%20monthly%20for%20their%20phone%20plan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20love%20the%20routine%20here.%20We%20love%20the%20predictability%2C%26quot%3B%20Allanach%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20see%20what%20Canada%20is%20offering%