bout%20tech%20being%20a%20young%20person's%20game%20is%20true.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2298fcebdc-4e30-439b-b939-0d52466dc45a%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20remember%20entering%20tech%20when%20it%20was%20a%20bunch%20of%20people%20who%20were%20passionate%20about%20computing%20and%20innovation%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20companies%20I%20worked%20for%20used%20to%20have%20initiatives%20that%20encouraged%20creativity%20and%20innovation%20within%20the%20company%20during%20company%20hours.%20This%20fostered%20a%20lot%20of%20new%20products.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20watched%20tech%20change%20before%20my%20eyes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20people%20from%20Wall%20Street%20and%20consulting%20firms%20saw%20that%20tech%20was%20a%20good%20industry%20to%20work%20in%2C%20they%20started%20to%20move%20into%20the%20tech%20landscape.%20In%202018%2C%20there%20was%20a%20tangible%20shift%20toward%20more%20profitable%20and%20cost-cutting%20programs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20rule%20of%20the%20nerds%20was%20over%20%E2%80%94%20the%20finance%20bros%20and%20accountants%20soon%20took%20over.%20They%20also%20brought%20their%20company%20culture%3A%20long%20hours%2C%20lots%20of%20face%20time%2C%20and%20lots%20of%20jargon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229c201bcf-201e-4f4a-9174-1adab5e59160%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI've%20been%20on%20medical%20leave%20for%20burnout%20twice%20in%20my%20career%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcity-vs-suburban-living-young-adult-zillennial-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EZillennial%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20I've%20seen%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Femployee-engagement-productivity-remote-work-hybrid-burnout-managers-office-expectations-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eburnout%20crisis%3C%2Fa%3E%20hit%20my%20generation.%20Many%20of%20us%20graduated%20when%20the%20economy%20was%20bad%2C%20and%20we%20didn't%20have%20the%20boundaries%20that%20Gen%20Z%20has%20in%20the%20workplace.%20We%20were%20taught%20to%20do%20what%20it%20takes%20to%20make%20the%20company%20happy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20June%202023%2C%20I%20went%20on%20short-term%20disability%20leave%20from%20the%20job%20I%20got%20after%20my%20FAANG%20layoff%20for%20burnout%20reasons.%20I%20just%20had%20to%20file%20basic%20paperwork%20for%20disability%20with%20HR.%20I%20also%20took%20medical%20leave%20earlier%20in%20my%20career%2C%20in%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20an%20employee%20on%20the%20ground%2C%20you%20can%20see%20and%20feel%20burnout%20and%20resentment%20in%20your%20fellow%20employees%2C%20and%20a%20distinct%20atmosphere%20of%20fear%20during%20every%20layoff%20and%20hiring%20freeze.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20people%20around%20me%20got%20laid%20off%2C%20I%20was%20expected%20to%20absorb%20their%20responsibilities.%20I%20had%20to%20interface%20with%20partners%20and%20clients%2C%20and%20the%20more%20people%20left%2C%20the%20more%20clients%20I%20had%20to%20take%20on%20without%20any%20additional%20pay.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2205d251b8-135b-409f-8410-0f4469506e19%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20was%20laid%20off%20again%20during%20my%20medical%20leave%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20to%20reevaluate%20my%20next%20move.%20I%20decided%20to%20leave%20tech%20and%20spend%20six%20months%20abroad%20learning%20about%20a%20new%20culture.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20went%20to%20a%20country%20where%20the%20US%20dollar%20was%20strong%2C%20and%20the%20people%20were%20hungry%20for%20new%20talent.%20I%20never%20had%20the%20personal%20time%20or%20opportunity%20to%20leave%20the%20US.%20Even%20though%20I'd%20submitted%20for%20transfers%20in%20some%20of%20my%20previous%20jobs%2C%20they%20were%20never%20approved.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20got%20a%20part-time%20job%20tutoring%20and%20teaching.%20There's%20a%20widespread%20shortage%20of%20teachers%2C%20especially%20in%20STEM.%20I%20saw%20a%20different%20way%20of%20living%20life%20and%20observed%20that%20we%20could%20institute%20more%20%3Ca%