0been%20touted%20as%20an%20example%20of%20a%20%26quot%3Bfounder%20mode%26quot%3B%20leader.%20%3Cp%3EJustin%20Sullivan%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFilip%20Dames%20is%20one%20tech%20figure%20who%20has%20found%20plenty%20that%20resonates%20with%20him%20in%20the%20founder%20mode%20philosophy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20founding%20partner%20at%20investment%20firm%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fearly-stage-tech-startups-capture-vc-attention-in-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECherry%20Ventures%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20part%20of%20the%20founding%20team%20of%20online%20retail%20firm%20Zalando%2C%20Dames%20has%20seen%20%26quot%3Befficiency%20go%20out%20the%20window%26quot%3B%20for%20startup%20leaders%20who%20bring%20in%2C%20say%2C%20a%20%26quot%3Bsuper%20senior%20sales%20guy%26quot%3B%20to%20solve%20problems%20as%20they%20grow%20in%20size.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20will%20never%20be%20as%20dedicated%2C%20they%20will%20never%20have%20as%20much%20skin%20in%20the%20game%2C%26quot%3B%20Dames%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BFor%20them%20it's%20a%20job%2C%20and%20for%20you%20as%20a%20founder%2C%20it's%20basically%20your%20life.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20idea%20gets%20to%20the%20heart%20of%20what%20the%20pro-founder%20mode%20camp%20prizes.%20In%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3Dia6Di_ytiSE%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epodcast%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Airbnb's%20Chesky%20argued%20that%20founders%20differ%20from%20managers%20by%20being%20the%20%26quot%3Bbiological%20parent%26quot%3B%20of%20the%20company%20they%20oversee.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20can%20love%20something%2C%20but%20when%20you're%20the%20biological%20parent%20of%20something%2C%20like%2C%20it%20came%20from%20you%2C%20it%20is%20you%2C%20there's%20a%20deep%20passion%20and%20love%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20tech%20leaders%20do%20become%20encumbered%20with%20a%20growing%20list%20of%20responsibilities%20as%20their%20companies%20grow.%20Big%20Tech%20firms%20like%20Meta%20and%20Google%20went%20on%20a%20huge%20hiring%20binge%20during%20the%20pandemic%20to%20meet%20the%20growing%20demand%20for%20digital%20services%2C%20but%20they%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftech-jobs-recession-layoffs-gen-z-students-class-of-2023-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esince%20laid%20off%20layers%20of%20middle%20managers.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Dames%2C%20growth%20doesn't%20necessarily%20mean%20companies%20and%20founders%20must%20switch%20to%20manager%20mode.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20view%2C%20many%20large%20companies%20where%20the%20CEO%20is%20the%20founder%20%26quot%3Bmanage%20to%20run%20things%20with%20the%20founder%20DNA%26quot%3B%20by%20ensuring%20the%20full%20organization%20works%20with%20the%20same%20clear%20%26quot%3Bvalues%26quot%3B%20in%20mind.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20eventually%20as%20the%20company%20grows%20the%20only%20way%20to%20do%20it%20is%20through%20values%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20value-led%20approach%20has%20been%20key%20for%20tech%20founders%20who%20have%20managed%20to%20maintain%20success%20at%20their%20companies%20years%20after%20they%20raised%20their%20initial%20round%20of%20seed%20money.%20Jeff%20Bezos%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20has%20famously%20retained%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faws.amazon.com%2Fexecutive-insights%2Fcontent%2Fhow-amazon-defines-and-operationalizes-a-day-1-culture%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmazon's%20%26quot%3BDay%201%26quot%3B%20culture%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20first%20established%20in%201997.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOthers%20see%20a%20risk%20in%20sticking%20to%20a%20single%20operating%20mode.%20According%20to%20Hussein%20Kanji%2C%20a%20founder%20and%20partner%20at%20venture%20capital%20firm%20Hoxton%20Ventures%2C%20it's%20easy%20to%20end%20up%20down%20the%20wrong%20track%20%26quot%3Bif%20you%20live%20just%20in%20one%20mode.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20love%20making%20things%20black%20and%20white%20when%20the%20world%20runs%20in%20a%20lot%20of%20different%20shades%20of%20truth%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BPeople%20have%20lost%20their%20ability%20to%20engage%20with%20seemingly%20contradictory%20ideas%20at%20the%20same%20time.%26quot%3B%20In%20his%20view%2C%20the%20best%20leaders%20are%20the%20ones%20who%20%26quot%3Bknow%20when%20it's%20time%20to%20be%20binary.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20view%20that%20tallies%20with%20Dames%2C%20though%20he%20sees%20founder%20mode%20leaders%20having%20more%20of%20an%20edge%20during%20times%20that%20call%20for%20a%20shift%20in%20approach.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20have%20more%20of%20the%20manager%20mindset%20and%20you're%20used%20to%20just%20calm%20waters%2C%20that%20makes%20things%20really%20difficult%20if%20you're%20in%20a%20fast-change%20environment%20and%20you%20need%20adaptability%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20reality%20just%20changes.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20said%2C%20some%20of%20the%20most%20successful%20tech%20companies%20right%20now%20are%20overseen%20by%20leaders%20who%20weren't%20their%20founders.%20Satya%20Nadella%20at%20Microsoft%20is%20one%20such%20leader%2C%20as%20is%20Dara%20Khosrowshahi%20at%20Uber.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222672%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Satya%20Nadella%20Microsoft%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F664cc6c414fb5b23cc5ebe7c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221426%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMicrosoft%20CEO%20Satya%20Nadella%20has%20led%20the%20company%20to%20new%20heights%20despite%20not%20being%20its%20founder.%3Cp%3EMicrosoft%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20unclear%20how%20Silicon%20Valley%20will%20resolve%20this%20debate.%20In%20an%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Fchamath%2Fstatus%2F1831003871344501069%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EX%20post%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0on%20Tuesday%2C%20venture%20capitalist%20Chamath%20Palihapitiya%20weighed%20in%20by%20dismissing%20Graham's%20categories%20and%20suggesting%20instead%20that%20there%20is%20%26quot%3Bfirst%20principles%20management%20and%20stupid%20management.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20your%20company%20isn't%20working%2C%20the%20only%20solution%20is%20to%20take%20the%20time%2C%20as%20laborious%20as%20it%20sounds%2C%20to%20break%20your%20business%20down%20to%20its%20core%20essentials%20and%20rebuild%20it%20from%20the%20ground%20up%20with%20zero%20nostalgia%20or%20loyalty%20to%20people%20or%20technology%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EExpect%20divides%20on%20the%20leadership%20merits%20of%20founders%20and%20managers%20to%20continue%20for%20some%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffounder-mode-manager-dividing-silicon-valley-2024-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1725526982000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66d96338289b805d1db47e48%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffounder-mode-manager-dividing-silicon-valley-2024-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Tech%20leaders%20have%20become%20engrossed%20in%20a%20debate%20over%20the%20best%20way%20to%20run%20their%20companies%20following%20an%20essay%20that%20championed%20%26quot%3Bfounder%20mode.%26quot%3B%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22hchowdhury%40insider.com%20(Hasan%20Chowdhury)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A6%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffounder-mode-manager-dividing-silicon-valley-2024-9%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Perimenopause%20symptoms%20turned%20me%20into%20a%20'zombie'%20at%2036.%20I'm%20angry%20I%20was%20robbed%20of%20precious%20time%20with%20my%20family.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22a%20collage%20of%20a%20womans%20mouth%20and%20a%20textured%20ink%20stain%2C%20placed%20on%20top%20of%20a%20harsh%20red%20background.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66bfc2641aa2ac29ee32081b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETech%20founder%20Ruth%20Shrauner%20said%20her%20perimenopause%20symptoms%20led%20her%20to%20feel%20like%20she%20was%20having%20an%20out-of-body%20experience.%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3B%20Chelsea%20Jia%20Feng%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ETech%20founder%20Ruth%20Shrauner%20faced%20severe%20perimenopause%20symptoms%20impacting%20her%20life%20and%20work.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShrauner%20initially%20mistook%20her%20symptoms%20for%20stress%20and%20struggled%20to%20find%20effective%20medical%20help.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBioidentical%20hormone%20replacement%20therapy%20helped%20her%20regain%20energy%20and%20emotional%20stability.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Ruth%20Shrauner%2C%20a%2037-year-old%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.poshedonthego.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Etech%20founder%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3Efrom%20Kansas%20City%2C%20Missouri.%20It's%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20paper%2C%20I'm%20a%20woman%20who's%20%26quot%3Bmade%20it.%26quot%3B%20I'm%20a%20first-generation%20college%20grad%20who%20built%20a%20multimillion-dollar%20digital%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-earn-six-figures-with-affiliate-marketing-websites-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaffiliate%20marketing%20business%3C%2Fa%3E%20online%20and%20launched%20my%20own%20tech%20startup%20company%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20typically%20the%20woman%20that%20other%20female%20business%20owners%20turn%20to%20for%20advice%20and%20a%20positive%20pep%20talk.%20So%2C%20in%20the%20fall%20of%202023%2C%20when%20I%20found%20myself%20lying%20in%20bed%20thinking%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20just%20want%20to%20go%20to%20sleep%20and%20never%20wake%20up%20again%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20felt%20like%20I%20was%20having%20an%20out-of-body%20experience.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20a%20terrifying%20moment%20that%20I%20now%20know%20was%20the%20result%20of%20early%20onset%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmy.clevelandclinic.org%2Fhealth%2Fdiseases%2F21608-perimenopause%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eperimenopause%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20the%20transitional%20period%20before%20menopause.%20It%20can%20happen%20to%20women%20between%20their%20mid-30s%20and%20mid-50s%20and%20cause%20both%20physical%20and%20emotional%20symptoms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a89d3417-5424-44f6-9935-8d8a1bdd8d99%5C%22%3EI%20thought%20the%20perimenopause%20symptoms%20were%20due%20to%20stress%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20symptoms%20started%20in%20early%202022%2C%20shortly%20after%20I%20turned%2036.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20energy%20started%20depleting.%20Little%20tasks%20felt%20like%20massive%20obstacles.%20Doing%20laundry%20seemed%20like%20the%20hardest%20job%20in%20the%20world%2C%20and%20making%20dinner%20felt%20excruciating.%20When%20I%20wasn't%20working%2C%20I'd%20lay%20on%20the%20couch%20as%20much%20as%20possible%20and%20pray%20that%20my%20toddler%20twins%20didn't%20need%20too%20much%20from%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20thought%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdoctor-shares-tips-for-being-heard-during-medical-visits-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Escheduling%20a%20doctor's%20appointment%3C%2Fa%3E%20seemed%20complex.%20The%20mental%20weight%20of%20the%20ever-growing%20list%20of%20daily%20tasks%20was%20heavy%2C%20constant%2C%20and%20draining.%20Soon%20this%20state%20of%20being%20became%20my%20new%20normal%20as%20my%20anxiety%20became%20more%20and%20more%20debilitating.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20there%20was%20the%20nightly%20insomnia.%20Despite%20being%20mentally%20and%20physically%20exhausted%2C%20I%20couldn't%20fall%20asleep%20before%2011%20p.m.%20on%20a%20normal%20night.%20Once%20I%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fhow-to-fall-asleep-fast%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efinally%20fell%20asleep%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I'd%20wake%20up%20around%202%20a.m.%20Sometimes%20I'd%20be%20extremely%20hot%20and%20sweaty%2C%20a%20tell-tale%20perimenopause%20symptom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20nights%2C%20I'd%20still%20be%20wide%20awake%20by%205%20a.m.%2C%20then%20I'd%20move%20downstairs%20to%20our%20couch%20and%20turn%20on%20Bravo%20TV%20to%20put%20me%20back%20to%20sleep.%20If%20lucky%2C%20I'd%20get%20another%20two%20hours%20of%20sleep%20before%20the%20kids%20woke%20up%20for%20the%20day.%20I'd%20get%20about%20five%20hours%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsleep-in-longer-healthier-life-according-to-science-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esleep%20on%20a%20good%20night%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20on%20most%20nights%2C%20I'd%20only%20get%20three%20to%20four%20hours%20of%20disrupted%20sleep.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226a3f921e-f3a1-4feb-845b-e4d27ece1904%5C%22%3EMy%20family%2C%20home%2C%20and%20social%20lives%20suffered%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20excitement%20for%20life%20also%20faded.%20While%20I%20still%20showed%20up%20to%20work%20on%20my%20multiple%20businesses%2C%20I%20felt%20numb%20most%20of%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESleep%20deprivation%20started%20cutting%20into%20my%20business%20day.%20On%20the%20worst%20nights%2C%20I'd%20go%20back%20to%20bed%20after%20my%20kids%20went%20to%20day%20care%2C%20or%20I'd%20sleep%20through%20their%20morning%20routine%20as%20my%20husband%20took%20care%20of%20them%20and%20got%20them%20out%20the%20door.%20There%20were%20plenty%20of%20days%20when%20I%20just%20didn't%20get%20out%20of%20bed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20my%20menstrual%20cycle%2C%20I'd%20have%20a%20few%20good%20days%20where%20I%20saw%20a%20glimmer%20of%20my%20old%20self.%20On%20those%20days%2C%20I'd%20feel%20motivated%20and%20excited%2C%20and%20I%20could%20accomplish%20what%20my%20former%20self%20was%20capable%20of.%20But%20most%20days%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fbrain-fog%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebrain%20fog%20and%20overwhelm%3C%2Fa%3E%20took%20over.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20brain%20was%20scrambled%20as%20it%20jumped%20from%20task%20to%20task.%20Things%20that%20used%20to%20be%20easy%20now%20felt%20like%20I%20was%20looking%20at%20a%20puzzle.%20I'd%20do%20enough%20to%20get%20by%20in%20my%20business%2C%20but%20not%20anything%20near%20what%20I'd%20been%20capable%20of%20producing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20saved%20every%20bit%20of%20my%20energy%20for%20work%20while%20my%20family%2C%20home%2C%20and%20social%20lives%20suffered.%20I%20had%20invested%20over%20%24150%2C000%20of%20my%20money%20into%20my%20tech%20startup%2C%20so%20I%20felt%20that%20there%20was%20no%20other%20option.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226e881eae-913f-4063-965b-4fc29504548a%5C%22%3ETrying%20to%20get%20help%20from%20doctors%20felt%20like%20an%20ongoing%20battle%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20easy%20to%20dismiss%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fmental-health%2Fstress-vs-anxiety%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esymptoms%20as%20stress%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Our%20twins%20were%20two-and-a-half%20years%20old%2C%20we%20were%20dealing%20with%20the%20recent%20loss%20of%20my%20brother%20and%20sister-in-law%20in%20a%20tragic%20accident%2C%20and%20I'd%20just%20taken%20the%20huge%20financial%20risk%20of%20launching%20my%20tech%20startup.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20saw%20multiple%20doctors%20and%20therapists%20on%20numerous%20occasions%20to%20try%20to%20address%20the%20insomnia%2C%20my%20concentration%20issues%2C%20and%20my%20overall%20lack%20of%20motivation%2C%20despite%20being%20on%20a%20high%20dosage%20of%20ADHD%20medication.%20None%20of%20the%20doctors%20I%20saw%20ever%20suggested%20that%20insomnia%20and%20night%20sweats%20were%20signs%20of%20hormonal%20imbalance%20or%20perimenopause.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20night%20in%20September%202023%2C%20I%20laid%20in%20bed%20wide%20awake%20and%20responded%20to%20an%20email%20at%203%3A30%20a.m.%20from%20Christine%20Ricci%2C%20a%20former%20nurse%20turned%20entrepreneur%20with%20whom%20I%20had%20a%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsc%2F4-steps-for-maximizing-your-relationship-with-a-business-mentor%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20business%20mentorship%3C%2Fa%3E%20meeting%20scheduled%20that%20next%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20our%20meeting%2C%20Christine%20mentioned%20my%20%26quot%3Bwee%20hours%26quot%3B%20email%2C%20and%20I%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BDoesn't%20everyone%20lay%20in%20bed%20wide%20awake%20from%202%20a.m.%20to%205%20a.m.%20every%20night%3F%26quot%3B%20She%20asked%20if%20I'd%20had%20my%20hormones%20checked%20while%20asking%20me%20about%20other%20symptoms%20that%20are%20related%20to%20perimenopause%20and%20hormonal%20imbalance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20this%2C%20I'd%20only%20heard%20women%20in%20their%2060s%20talk%20about%20night%20sweats%2C%20hot%20flashes%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Freproductive-health%2Fmenopause-age%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emenopause%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20didn't%20think%20it%20was%20something%20I%20had%20to%20worry%20about%20for%20another%2020%20years.%20But%20when%20I%20researched%20symptoms%20for%20perimenopause%2C%20I%20found%20an%20infographic%20mentioning%20all%20of%20the%20symptoms%20I'd%20been%20experiencing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ea2225da-b11e-40f9-8136-017497e32ea8%5C%22%3EI%20felt%20a%20tiny%20glimmer%20of%20hope%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EChristine's%20company%20had%20just%20partnered%20with%20Dr.%20Daved%20Rosenswet%2C%20a%20hormone%20specialist%20who%20spent%20most%20of%20his%20career%20researching%20and%20treating%20menopause%20through%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Freproductive-health%2Fhormone-replacement-therapy%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebioidentical%20hormone%20replacement%20therapy%3C%2Fa%3E%20(BHRT).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20agreed%20to%20meet%20with%20the%20team%20to%20see%20if%20hormone%20replacement%20therapy%20was%20a%20good%20option%20for%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20completing%20my%20intake%20survey%20and%20interview%2C%20Christine%20and%20Dr.%20Rosenswet's%20team%20worked%20to%20analyze%2C%20diagnose%2C%20and%20create%20a%20BHRT%20plan%20for%20me.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgynecologist-jen-gunter-on-startups-tackling-menopause-2021-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFinding%20the%20right%20hormonal%20balance%3C%2Fa%3E%20takes%20patience%20and%20needs%20to%20be%20individualized%20for%20every%20woman.%20I%20was%20prescribed%20Bi-est%20(a%20topical%20estrogen%20cream)%2C%20progesterone%2C%20and%20testosterone%20oils%20to%20treat%20my%20early-onset%20perimenopause%20diagnosis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EEditor's%20note%3A%20Bi-est%20is%20not%20FDA-approved.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20told%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmy.clevelandclinic.org%2Fhealth%2Ftreatments%2F15660-bioidentical-hormones%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epotential%20side%20effects%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20BHRT%2C%20including%20mood%20swings%2C%20bloating%2C%20insomnia%2C%20and%20sleepiness%20%E2%80%94%20all%20the%20symptoms%20I%20was%20already%20experiencing.%20I%20did%20a%20lot%20of%20research%20and%20decided%20to%20proceed%20with%20the%20treatment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224123c48c-8607-413d-a7a8-389b0eb049b1%5C%22%3EIt%20felt%20like%20I%20was%20coming%20out%20of%20a%20heavy%20fog%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20BHRT%2C%20I%20began%20to%20experience%20emotions%20again.%20I%20felt%20excited%2C%20happy%2C%20alive%2C%20energized%2C%20motivated%2C%20passionate%2C%20sad%2C%20angry%20%E2%80%94%20all%20of%20the%20feelings%20that%20had%20been%20replaced%20by%20a%20constant%20feeling%20of%20nothingness%20from%20perimenopause.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20a%20month%20of%20treatment%2C%20I%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftips-for-getting-better-sleep-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eable%20to%20fall%20asleep%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20a%20decent%20hour%20and%20could%20sleep%20through%20the%20entire%20night.%20I%20no%20longer%20woke%20up%20with%20night%20sweats%20or%20racing%20thoughts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELooking%20back%20on%20the%20year%20and%20a%20half%20prior%2C%20I%20couldn't%20believe%20how%20bad%20my%20emotions%20and%20executive%20functions%20had%20gotten.%20It%20was%20as%20if%20I'd%20been%20a%20walking%20zombie%20who%20couldn't%20see%20or%20think%20clearly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20been%20on%20BHRT%20for%20nine%20months%20now%2C%20and%20the%20relief%20I%20feel%20makes%20me%20want%20to%20burst%20out%20in%20happy%20tears.%20I'm%20not%20sure%20how%20long%20people%20normally%20stay%20on%20BHRT%2C%20but%20after%20at%20least%2010%20years%20I%20plan%20to%20get%20a%20yearly%20evaluation%20of%20the%20risks%20and%20benefits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ee699526-533a-4d77-b713-9388ed5213e4%5C%22%3EWomen's%20health%20education%20isn't%20prioritized%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20I'm%20so%20happy%20to%20feel%20like%20myself%20again%2C%20I've%20experienced%20a%20lot%20of%20anger%20as%20I%20learn%20more%20about%20the%20lack%20of%20education%20and%20empathy%20surrounding%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsupplements-dietitian-women-health-specialist-regimen-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewomen's%20health%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20angry%20that%20it%20took%20me%20a%20year%20and%20a%20half%20to%20find%20answers%20even%20though%20I%20kept%20advocating%20for%20myself%20to%20multiple%20doctors.%20I'm%20angry%20that%20women's%20health%20education%20isn't%20prioritized%20during%20medical%20school%2C%20in%20the%20medical%20community%2C%20or%20in%20clinical%20studies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20of%20all%2C%20I'm%20angry%20that%20perimenopause%20robbed%20me%20of%20precious%20time%20with%20my%20husband%20and%20kids%20that%20I'll%20never%20get%20back.%20I%20felt%20so%20much%20shame%20for%20being%20a%20zombie%20mom%20during%20those%20years%2C%20but%20now%20I%20understand%20that%20it%20wasn't%20something%20I%20could%20control%20or%20%26quot%3Bmindset%20coach%26quot%3B%20my%20way%20out%20of.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20connected%20with%20and%20learned%20from%20other%20women%20who%20have%20had%20similar%20experiences.%20I%20hope%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcarli-lloyd-advocating-more-options-women-healthcare-2022-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewomen%20stop%20masking%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20making%20excuses%20for%20their%20symptoms.%20Rather%2C%20we%20must%20listen%20to%20our%20intuitions%20when%20we%20don't%20feel%20like%20ourselves.%20I'd%20recommend%20that%20women%20experiencing%20perimenopause%20symptoms%20go%20to%20a%20functional%20doctor%20or%20a%20hormone%20therapy%20specialist.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%20of%20blaming%20hormones%20for%20making%20women%20crazy%20or%20lazy%2C%20I%20hope%20that%20society%20begins%20to%20see%20hormones%20as%20a%20gift%20that%20gives%20women%20unique%20superpowers%20that%20can%20be%20used%20to%20impact%20our%20small%20pieces%20of%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EIf%20you%20have%20gone%20through%20the%20process%20of%20identifying%20unknown%20health%20symptoms%20that%20affect%20your%20work%20and%20personal%20life%20and%20would%20like%20to%20share%20your%20story%2C%20email%20Jane%20Zhang%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Ajanezhang%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Ejanezhang%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fperimenopause-symptoms-tech-founder-shares-treatment-2024-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1725526982000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66bfc2641aa2ac29ee32081b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fperimenopause-symptoms-tech-founder-shares-treatment-2024-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20tech%20founder%20shares%20her%20journey%20through%20perimenopause%2C%20highlighting%20how%20the%20symptoms%20impacted%20her%20family%20and%20business%2C%20and%20how%20she%20found%20treatment.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Robin%20Madell)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A7%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fperimenopause-symptoms-tech-founder-shares-treatment-2024-9%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Investor%20Who%20Risked%20It%20All%20On%20'Black%20Myth%3A%20Wukong'%20Now%20Minting%20Millions%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EBlack%20Myth%3A%20Wukong%20has%20sold%2018%20million%20copies%20in%20two%20weeks%20-%20one%20of%20the%20fastest%20starts%20the%20global%20gaming%20industry%20has%20seen.%20That%20record%20pace%20has%20in%20turn%20minted%20millions%20for%20its%20earliest%20and%20biggest%20investor.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWukong%20was%20a%20leap%20of%20faith%20for%20Daniel%20Wu%2C%20whose%20little-known%20Hero%20Games%20is%20the%20biggest%20external%20shareholder%20in%20creator%20Game%20Science.%20His%20startup%20stuck%20with%20its%20partner%20through%20years%20of%20flops%20and%20contributed%20a%20large%20chunk%20of%20the%20blockbuster%20title's%20%2470%20million%20budget%20over%20six%20years%20of%20development%2C%20an%20unheard-of%20undertaking%20for%20a%20Chinese%20project.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20paid%20off%20big%20time.%20The%20action%20game%20based%20on%20the%20legend%20of%20the%20Monkey%20King%20has%20outsold%20industry%20icons%20such%20as%20Elden%20Ring%20and%20Zelda%2C%20at%20least%20in%20its%20initial%20spurt.%20It%20can%20reach%2030%20million%20sales%20over%20its%20lifetime%2C%20augmented%20with%20an%20expansion%20to%20come%2C%20Wu%20told%20Bloomberg%20News.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChina's%20biggest%20PC%20creation%20emerged%20from%20a%20creative%20team%20whose%20biggest%20claim%20to%20fame%20before%20this%20summer%20was%20a%20visit%20from%20Apple%20Inc.'s%20Tim%20Cook.%20Wu%2C%20who%20escorted%20the%20iPhone%20boss%20around%20Hero's%20Shanghai%20offices%20in%202017%2C%20said%20one%20of%20its%20early%20collaborations%20with%20Game%20Science%20caught%20Cook's%20eye%20-%20though%20that%20project%20ultimately%20tanked.%20It%20took%20another%20four%20years%20before%20Tencent%20Holdings%20Ltd.%20invested%20in%20Hero's%20investee%2C%20after%20a%20tantalizing%20Wukong%20trailer.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20Game%20Science%20is%20worth%20several%20billion%20yuan%2C%20Wu%20said%2C%20marking%20a%20return%20of%20several-fold%20on%20his%20studio's%2020%25%20stake.%20Hero%20Games%20had%20paid%20just%2060%20million%20yuan%20(%248.5%20million)%20for%20its%20slice%20in%202017.%20Both%20startups%20find%20themselves%20unexpectedly%20in%20the%20spotlight%2C%20hailed%20for%20finally%20showing%20China%20is%20capable%20of%20producing%20a%20big-budget%20title%20on%20par%20with%20the%20best%20of%20the%20West.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20want%20to%20hear%20the%20truth%2C%20Game%20Science's%20success%20today%20is%20built%20upon%20its%20four%20failures%20in%20a%20row%2C%26quot%3B%20the%2036-year-old%20Wu%20said%20in%20an%20exclusive%20interview%20from%20his%20Beijing%20office.%20%26quot%3BWukong%20proves%20not%20only%20that%20we%20have%20top-notch%20game-making%20capabilities%2C%20but%20also%20we%20can%20tell%20a%20good%20story%20with%20Chinese%20elements.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20Wu%2C%20who%20gave%20up%20a%20career%20as%20a%20startup%20financier%20to%20immerse%20himself%20in%20games%20close%20to%20a%20decade%20ago%2C%20Wukong%20is%20much%20more%20than%20just%20a%20groundbreaking%20game.%20He%20and%20Game%20Science%20co-founder%20Feng%20Ji%2C%20five%20years%20his%20elder%2C%20tied%20their%20fortunes%20to%20the%20success%20of%20a%20title%20built%20for%20consoles%20and%20PCs%2C%20in%20a%20country%20dominated%20by%20mobile%20entertainment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-09%2Fhp0nh4oc_hero-games-office-bloomberg_625x300_05_September_24.jpg%3Fim%3DFaceCrop%2Calgorithm%3Ddnn%2Cwidth%3D1200%2Cheight%3D738%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20its%20release%20on%20Aug.%2020%2C%20the%20game%20has%20broken%20several%20records%20for%20single-player%20titles%2C%20eclipsing%20the%20likes%20of%20Cyberpunk%202077%20with%20runaway%20popularity%20at%20home%20in%20China.%20It's%20estimated%20to%20have%20earned%20%24700%20million%20so%20far%2C%20overshadowed%20only%20by%20Call%20of%20Duty's%20historic%20%241%20billion%20in%2010%20days%2C%20according%20to%20Niko%20Partners%20analyst%20Daniel%20Ahmad.%20He%20sees%20overseas%20sales%20accounting%20for%20a%20larger%20share%20going%20forward%20as%20the%20game's%20global%20renown%20grows.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWukong%20got%20a%20lift%20from%20state%20media%20lauding%20its%20faithful%20depiction%20of%20historic%20and%20cultural%20sites%2C%20but%20success%20came%20only%20after%20Wu%20and%20Feng%20risked%20everything%20to%20realize%20the%20project.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20were%20two%20drowning%20rats%2C%26quot%3B%20Wu%2C%20whose%20company%20is%20still%20not%20profitable%2C%20said%20of%20himself%20and%20Feng.%20%26quot%3BNeither%20of%20us%20was%20afraid%20of%20failure%2C%20and%20he%20already%20knew%20his%20next%20step.%20The%20only%20thing%20is%20that%20he%20needed%20me%20to%20place%20even%20bigger%20bets.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGame%20Science%20had%20struck%20out%20with%20its%20three%20prior%20efforts%2C%20which%20were%20more%20modest%20free-to-play%20mobile%20games%20chasing%20attention%20in%20the%20world's%20biggest%20games%20arena.%20One%20of%20them%2C%20Art%20of%20War%3A%20Red%20Tides%2C%20even%20got%20prime%20placement%20on%20the%20iOS%20App%20Store%20after%20Cook's%20visit%2C%20but%20to%20no%20avail.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20sole%20investor%20and%20publishing%20partner%20of%20Game%20Science%2C%20Hero%20Games%20took%20significant%20losses%2C%20but%20Wu%20didn't%20shy%20away%20in%202018%20when%20Feng%2C%20now%20his%20late-night%20League%20of%20Legends%20teammate%2C%20reached%20out%20for%20more%20money%20to%20craft%20an%20ambitious%20project%20then%20codenamed%20Black%20Myth%20One.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20won't%20take%20another%20six%20years%20for%20the%20next%20chapter%20in%20what's%20planned%20to%20be%20a%20series%20based%20on%20Chinese%20mythology%20-%20though%20that%20won't%20be%20a%20sequel%2C%20Wu%20said.%20Game%20Science%20is%20working%20on%20an%20expansion%20to%20Wukong%2C%20which%20will%20give%20it%20a%20chance%20to%20monetize%20the%20game%20a%20second%20time.%202022's%20Elden%20Ring%2C%20a%20title%20with%20similar%20play%20style%20and%20design%2C%20has%20shown%20how%20the%20release%20of%20an%20expansion%20-%20this%20year's%20Shadow%20of%20the%20Erdtree%20-%20can%20spur%20a%20fresh%20flurry%20of%20sales%20for%20the%20original.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWu%20co-founded%20Hero%20Games%20in%202015%20after%20a%20three-year%20stint%20with%20famed%20Chinese%20venture%20firm%20ZhenFund.%20He%20zeroed%20in%20on%20Feng%20and%20his%20Game%20Science%20team%20early%20on%2C%20describing%20them%20as%20an%20asset%20he%20couldn't%20afford%20to%20miss%20out%20on.%20At%20Tencent%2C%20Feng%20had%20led%20a%20team%20of%20250%20people%20on%20the%20development%20of%20online%20role-playing%20game%20Asura%2C%20inspired%20by%20similar%20folklore%20to%20Wukong.%20The%20title%20launched%20in%202010%20and%20initially%20won%20praise%20for%20its%20design%2C%20though%20it%20later%20upset%20players%20with%20practices%20around%20its%20in-game%20shop%20that%20were%20deemed%20exploitative.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHero%20Games%2C%20which%20orchestrated%20a%20marketing%20blitz%20around%20Wukong%20that%20included%20Luckin%20Coffee%20giveaways%2C%20also%20drew%20criticism%20outside%20of%20China%20for%20its%20guidance%20to%20streamers%20playing%20Wukong%20to%20not%20discuss%20%26quot%3Bfeminist%20propaganda%2C%26quot%3B%20politics%20or%20Covid-19.%20Wu%20declined%20to%20comment%20on%20the%20matter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%202%2C000-person%20Hero%20Games%20team%2C%20even%20with%20that%20huge%20winning%20bet%20in%20its%20portfolio%2C%20isn't%20making%20a%20profit.%20Wu's%20company%20is%20on%20a%20yearslong%20transition%20from%20publisher%20to%20developer%2C%20and%20it's%20facing%20the%20same%20challenges%20that%20Game%20Science%20ran%20into%20when%20trying%20to%20score%20a%20mobile%20hit.%20Until%20it%20breaks%20through%2C%20Wu's%20message%20to%20staff%20this%20year%20will%20be%20to%20learn%20to%20embrace%20the%20death%20of%20your%20project.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20the%20most%20gruesome%20year%20for%20China's%20games%20industry%20ever%2C%26quot%3B%20Wu%20said%2C%20noting%20the%20large%20number%20of%20unsuccessful%20games%20that%20few%20will%20ever%20see%20or%20hear%20about.%20The%20country's%20economic%20difficulties%20have%20cut%20into%20entertainment%20spending%20and%20forced%20many%20studios%20to%20reconsider%20or%20abandon%20projects.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20makes%20the%20triumph%20of%20Wukong%20all%20the%20sweeter.%20Wu%20expects%20it%20will%20fire%20up%20passions%20and%20interest%20to%20create%20more%20games%20based%20China's%20rich%20history%20and%20culture%20-%20and%20more%20courage%20to%20build%20for%20consoles.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20Wu%20encountered%20the%20first%20big%20fight%20in%20Wukong%20on%20his%20PlayStation%205%2C%20he%20texted%20Feng%20to%20say%20he%20was%20welling%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp