20up%20all%20the%20spare%20compute%20and%20put%20it%20to%20work%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThink%20about%20what%20Uber%20did%20for%20cars%2C%20what%20Airbnb%20did%20for%20homes.%20I%20think%20w.ai%20is%20doing%20something%20similar%20for%20computers%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Benkhin.%20The%20project%20is%20in%20its%20infancy%2C%20but%20in%20theory%20he%20says%20users%20will%20be%20able%20to%20download%20an%20app%2C%20hit%20a%20button%2C%20and%20then%20sit%20back%20and%20get%20paid%20for%20their%20unused%20processing%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20want%20to%20make%20this%20extremely%20easy%20for%20people%2C%20my%20mom%20should%20be%20able%20to%20do%20this%2C%26quot%3B%20Benkhin%20said.%20He%20says%20he%20got%20the%20idea%20when%20he%20realized%20how%20much%20money%20Wombo%20and%20other%20companies%20were%20paying%20to%20big%20cloud%20providers%20like%20AWS%2C%20Google%2C%20and%20Microsoft%2C%20which%20effectively%20control%20the%20supply%20of%20computing%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20asked%20himself%3A%20what%20if%20he%20could%20sidestep%20those%20gatekeepers%20and%20utilize%20a%20powerful%20but%20scattered%20resource%20that%20was%20laying%20dormant%20all%20around%20him%3F%20The%20idea%20presents%20a%20daunting%20technical%20challenge%3A%20how%20to%20take%20the%20workload%20for%20an%20intensive%20AI%20task%2C%20slice%20it%20up%20into%20a%20million%20little%20pieces%2C%20distribute%20it%20to%20smartphones%2C%20laptops%2C%20and%20gaming%20consoles%20worldwide%2C%20and%20then%20reassemble%20it%20quickly%20and%20reliably.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20he%20can%20figure%20it%20out%2C%20Benkhin%20thinks%20it%20could%20be%20a%20viable%20alternative%20to%20the%20big%20cloud%20providers.%20He%20also%20sees%20it%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bprimitive%20UBI%26quot%3B%20with%20users%20getting%20paid%20for%20their%20idle%20machines%20and%20for%20simply%20being%20a%20part%20of%20the%20network.%20His%20ultimate%20vision%2C%20though%2C%20is%20for%20a%20world%20where%20AI%2C%20much%20like%20th